title: johnny cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Cut in or blend in shortening; add milk.
Pour into a well-greased iron frying pan.
Cook on top of stove, turning only once.
Alternate method is to bake at 350°.

title: frozen strawberry yogurt pie
directions: Fold yogurt into whipped topping and blend well.
Fold in strawberries; spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm.
Garnish with additional whole strawberries.
Let stand at room temperature for 10 minutes before serving.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to box directions. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan lined with waxed paper. Cool about 20 minutes in pan, then invert. Completely cool cake. Slice in half lengthwise and separate.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: baked apples
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Wash and core the apples. Place the apples in a baking pan. Cover the bottom of the pan with 1/4-inch of water. Place 1/4 teaspoon of butter, 1 teaspoon of honey and sprinkle of cinnamon into the center of each apple. Bake for 35 minutes or until apples can be easily pierced with a fork.

title: no-bake peanut butter cookies
directions: In medium saucepan, combine sugar and corn syrup. Bring to full boil. Immediately remove from heat. Stir in cereal and peanut butter. Shape into balls or drop by teaspoon onto wax paper. Double recipe for extra cookies.

title: savory topped franks
directions: Mash potatoes; add salad dressing, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, celery, onions and pickle; mix lightly.
Season to taste.
Fill franks with potato mixture.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Bring crushed pineapple to a boil.
Dissolve the 2 packages of jello in this.
Remove from heat; add cherries (including juice) and 12 ounce Coke.
Let congeal.
You can add 1/2 cup nuts if desired.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed.
Combine pasta and remaining ingredients and toss.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add sugar, vanilla and oil; blend well.
Stir in zucchini.
Stir together flour, baking powder, salt, baking soda and cinnamon.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Fold in the nuts.
Turn into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks to small bowl.
Add all other ingredients except paprika.
Mash with fork to blend well.
Fill egg whites with mixture.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika.

title: seasoned parmesan popcorn
directions: Mix together margarine and seasoning.
Drizzle over popcorn. Toss until well coated.
Add cheese.
Toss to coat evenly (2 quarts).

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Bring water and margarine to a boil.
Stir in flour until it forms a ball.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Spread out on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Pat down large bubbles as soon as you take it out of the oven.
Cool until it softens.

title: loretta lynn's gooey cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions.
While still warm, poke holes in cake with a wooden spoon handle, about 1-inch apart halfway into cake, not to bottom.
Pour sweetened condensed milk into holes.

title: yogurt and chiffon cake
directions: Beat yolks of 8 large eggs.
Add 2/3 cup sugar and poppy seed. Beat until thick.
Add alternately 1 cup flour and yogurt.
Set aside.

title: spicy turkey roast
directions: Remove mesh from the turkey.
Lay turkey out as flat as possible on a cutting board, skin side down.
Combine the garlic, rosemary, pepper and salt in a food processor, with the steel blade in place or in a blender.
Turn motor on.
Add the oil, processing until coarsely chopped.
Spread half the garlic mixture over the inside of the turkey.
Reroll the turkey.
Tie firmly with string every two inches to return the meat to its original log shape. Spread evenly with the remaining garlic mixture.
Place on a rack in a roasting pan.
Roast at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours until a meat thermometer inserted in the center registers 170°.
A long log shape takes less time than a more compact roast.
Remove from the oven.
Let stand 20 minutes before removing string.
Cut thin slices to serve.
Garnish with rosemary and red pepper.
Scrape up cooking juices from bottom of pan.
Spoon over meat, or thicken with flour and add chicken broth for a gravy, if desired. Preparation time:
25 minutes.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Add flour and cornmeal and mix well.
Bake in pans with covers or place a cookie sheet on top of bread pan.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with coconut and pecan pieces. Mix German chocolate cake mix according to directions.
Spread over pecans and coconut.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with 1 layer of whole graham crackers. Mix pudding and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour mixture on top of crackers.
Cover with another layer of crackers.
Spread frosting on top.
Let sit in the refrigerator for several hours.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in water.
Blend cheese, flour and bouillon cubes.
Add to broccoli.
Heat and add half-and-half.

title: spanish dip
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain off grease. Add the next 5 ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. This is a great dip for crackers, vegetables, meat balls, just anything. Also, great as a sauce!

title: christmas tortoni
directions: Mix cookie crumbs, almonds and 1/4 cup candied cherries; fold into ice cream.
Divide into 8 muffin cups, lined with paper cups. Decorate with candied cherries.
Freeze about 4 hours or until firm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add sugar and dissolve.
Let cool.
Then put in other mixture and let stand for 2 hours.
Add ice and ginger ale before serving.

title: quick dirty rice
directions: Saute ground meat, onion and bell pepper.
Mix with rice, mushroom soup and chicken soup.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° in a 3-quart casserole dish.

title: bean and macaroni stew
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 2-quart saucepan.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 15 minutes, stirring occasionally, until pasta is tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: quick chicken and egg soup
directions: Dissolve chicken bouillon in 4 cups boiling water.
Crack open eggs and add to water, one at a time.
Cook for 2 minutes. Meanwhile, cook noodles in separate pan and drain.
Add Lipton soup mix to bouillon mixture.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add drained noodles.
Serve hot with grated Romano cheese.

title: chicken pizzazz
directions: Brown chicken in skillet.
Put soup, onions, 1/2 can water and Tabasco sauce in with chicken.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Add tomatoes and noodles.
Cook another 15 minutes or until noodles are done.

title: patti's broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Lay in baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients in pan.
Heat just to simmer.
Pour over broccoli. Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: poulet d'artichoke
directions: Drain
artichoke
hearts
and
arrange in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.	Spread	chicken
on top.
Combine the soup, mayonnaise and
lemon
juice and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese. Toss bread crumbs with butter and place on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Combine cake mix, 2 eggs and margarine.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cream cheese, 2 eggs and confectioners sugar.
Spread over mix; sprinkle with chopped nuts. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Let cool completely.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onion together with enough water to cover until tender.
Mash with a potato masher and add margarine, salt, pepper and milk.
Cover and simmer until good and hot.

title: hot macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; cool.
When cool, mix macaroni and remaining ingredients, except for 1/2 cup cheese.
Pour into greased square pan.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake for 30 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar gradually.
Add vanilla.
Beat well until lemony color.
Add dry ingredients, blending well.
Heat milk and butter or margarine up to a boil.
Pour into batter quickly and blend well.
Bake in a greased and floured pan (9 x 9 x 2-inch) for 30 minutes or until done at 350°.

title: french silk fudge
directions: In top of double boiler, melt chocolate over hot water. Remove from heat.
Add sweetened condensed milk, vanilla, salt and desired nuts.
Stir until smooth.
Turn into wax paper lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill.
Cut in one inch squares.
Store in airtight container.
Yields 48 pieces.

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in a medium-sized heavy saucepan.
Beat yolks, milk and water with whisk until well blended.
Stir into sugar mixture.
Whisk constantly over medium heat about 5 minutes, until thick and boiling.
Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Whisk until well-blended.
Let stand at room temperature for 15 minutes or until slightly cooled, stirring 3 times.
Pour into crust; cover loosely with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight.

title: hamburg stroganoff
directions: Saute onion in butter and garlic over medium heat.
Add meat and brown.
Add flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
(Should be a little thick.)
Add a little water, if necessary.
Cook 5 minutes. Add soup.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and heat through.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: glenhorn oatcakes
directions: Blend dry ingredients.
Blend with water and shortening into a dough.
Roll out 1/4 to 1/3-inch thick.
Cut into squares.
Bake on ungreased sheet at 350° for 15 minutes only.
Makes approximately 1 dozen large cakes.

title: fat-free chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
In separate bowl, whisk egg whites, water and corn syrup.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Spray 9-inch square pan with cooking spray and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine.
Mix with crumbs and press into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine remaining margarine with sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat 15 minutes.
Pour onto crumb mixture.
Layer pineapple and bananas, then berries.
Top with Cool Whip and nuts. Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: quick and easy linguini
directions: Cook linguini in boiling, salted water.
Drain and rinse. While linguini is cooking, separate meat pieces.
Mix together the eggs and milk in small container.
In a large pan over high heat, melt butter.
Add mushrooms and meat with salt and pepper.
Saute. Add linguini, stirring to coat.
Add liquid mixture.
Stir constantly for 5 to 10 minutes or until thickened.
Serve immediately.

title: spicy cream cheese frosting
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Add butter and beat until light and fluffy.
Gradually add sugar.
Stir in remaining ingredients and continue beating until thoroughly blended.

title: creamy broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Steam broccoli; cut up cheese.
Cut up broccoli.
Mix soups and Miracle Whip and cheese.
Spread broccoli out in pan.
Spread creamed ingredients over, cover and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 300°.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and let stand 1 hour.
Chop fresh vegetables and dip.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Let pie crusts come to room temperature.
Press one crust into a deep-dish pie pan.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie crust.
Top with another pie crust and fold under.
Bake at 350° until crust is golden brown.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine until clear.
Steam zucchini until almost tender.
Add all ingredients and place in buttered casserole.
Top with buttered bread crumbs and 2 tablespoons sunflower seeds.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling hot water.
Add ice cubes and apricot halves, juice and all.
Stir well.
Add the cup of marshmallows on top.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: nutmeg feather cake
directions: Mix butter, Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Stir together flour, baking powder, salt, soda, nutmeg and 1 cup buttermilk with this mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350°.

title: crawfish casserole
directions: Saute onions, bell pepper, celery and 2 tablespoons margarine.
Mash Ro-Tel tomatoes, add and steam for about 10 minutes.
Add prepared rice, soup and crawfish tails.
Add parsley and place mixture in casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese and bake for 40 minutes at 325°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pot bean dinner
directions: Brown ground beef and drain; place in crock-pot.
Brown bacon and onions.
Drain and place into crock-pot.
Add all ingredients; mix well.
Cook on low for 4 to 6 hours.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Fry bacon and crumble into small pieces.
Cut up broccoli and cauliflower.
Add bacon and shredded Cheddar cheese.
Mix sugar with Miracle Whip until smooth.
Mix all together.

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and put into chocolate crust.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add soup to the meat and place meat mixture in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place green beans or peas on top of meat, then layer the mashed potatoes on top of the vegetables.
Bake at 350° until heated through.

title: peanut butter crisscross
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs; beat thoroughly.
Stir in peanut butter.
Sift dry ingredients together and stir in.
Form in balls on ungreased cookie sheet; press with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Combine salad dressing mix, sour cream, and mayonnaise. Set aside.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix all and drop by teaspoon onto baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Reduce speed and add coconut milk.
Add vanilla and continue mixing.
Combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to above mixture.
Beat just enough to combine.
Add egg whites and beat just until smooth (don't overbeat).
Bake in 3 pans at 350°.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Rinse in cool water.
Mix with other ingredients.
Use Salad Supreme seasoning according to taste.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute ground beef; drain.
Add tomatoes sauce, 3 cans water, tomato paste, onion, bell pepper, celery, mushrooms, garlic cloves and Italian seasoning.
Add salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Cook on low heat 2 to 3 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Mix graham crackers, powdered sugar and melted butter; put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix eggs, sugar and cream cheese; put on top of crust.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Spread with can of blueberry pie mix.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pasta, pepper and broccoli salad
directions: Prepare macaroni as directed.
Drain.
Keep warm.
Saute in 1 tablespoon olive oil and red peppers until crisp.
Remove to bowl. In same skillet, use 1 tablespoon oil and 1/2 teaspoon salt to cook broccoli, stirring constantly until coated with oil.
Add 3/4 cup water.
Reduce heat, cover and cook for 5 minutes, until tender-crisp, stirring often.

title: cowboy corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Put oil in cast-iron skillet. Combine cornmeal mix, egg, milk and oil in bowl and blend together. Pour half in skillet. Add peppers, onion and grated cheese. Add rest of corn bread and bake 25 minutes.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Blend well.
Roll into balls size of quarters.
Place on shallow baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: tuscany crostini
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding parsley and jack cheese last. Spread on baquette slices and put under the broiler until bubbly and lightly toasted.
Serve immediately.

title: beef stew
directions: Boil beef in a large pot for approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Peel, cut and add potatoes to pot.
Add fresh carrots, corn and celery. Let cook for one hour.
Add tomato sauce and tomato paste.
Let cook for 15 minutes.
Slice tomatoes and place on top of stew.
Let simmer for 15 minutes or until the soup has thickened.
Can be served over a bed of rice or by itself.

title: creamy pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large bowl, combine pumpkin, sweetened condensed milk, eggs and spices.
Mix well and pour into pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes; reduce oven to 350° and continue baking 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted 1-inch from edge comes out clean.
Cool thoroughly before cutting.
Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: taco salad dip
directions: Spread beans in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mash avocados and add lemon juice and sour cream.
Spread over beans.
Add other ingredients in layers as listed on recipe.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Mix together and pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: linda jackson's pretzel salad
directions: Make a crust of the pretzels, margarine (melted) and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake 10 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: pralines
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Cook until soft ball stage. Remove from heat and stir in last ingredients.
Beat until mixture grains.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: golfer's stew(5 hour stew)
directions: Combine meat and vegetables in large casserole dish.
Combine juice, salt, sugar and tapioca.
Pour over stew.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours.
No peeking.

title: frozen strawberry dessert
directions: Mix until crumbly. Then put in a large, flat pan. Place in oven at 400° for 15 minutes. Stir every 5 minutes to keep from burning. Then pat about 3/4 of this mixture on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Save 1/4 to sprinkle on top.

title: quick monkey bread
directions: Sprinkle pecans in bottom of a well-greased 10-inch Bundt pan. Set aside.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Cut biscuits into quarters.
Roll each piece in sugar mixture and lay in pan. Combine brown sugar and 1/2 cup of butter.
Pour over dough.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool bread 10 minutes in pan, then invert into serving plate.

title: ants on a stump
directions: Cut the apples into fourths. Spread some peanut butter on the apple slices. Stick some raisins on the peanut butter. Enjoy the healthy snack!

title: banana bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and softened butter.
Add bananas, vanilla and milk.
Mix in flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Stir in nuts. Put in one large or 2 small loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet minglers
directions: In a large microwave-safe bowl, melt chocolate at High for 1 minute.
Stir and heat an additional 30 seconds at High or until melted.
Stir in peanut butter and peanuts.
Pour mixture over cereal.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Arrange ribs in roasting pan. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over ribs. Cover and bake in 325° oven 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: almost mom's meat pie
directions: Cook meat and drain off grease.
Set aside.
Boil potatoes and onion until soft.
Drain (reserve some liquid) and mash to a runny consistency.
(Add some of the drained liquid, if too dry.) Mix in cooked meat and spices.
If you make your own crust, use a little less Crisco.
If you are using premade crust follow instructions for a 2 crust pie.
Bake on lower oven shelf at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Cook beef and onion in oil until meat is brown and crumbly. Stir in soup, catsup, water, salt, oregano, garlic powder and pepper.
Simmer about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: bubble pizza
directions: Brown meat, drain.
Stir in pizza sauce.
Quarter the biscuits and place in greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish.
Top with beef mixture.

title: apple crunch
directions: Mix until crumbled; put over apples.
Melt 1 stick oleo and pour over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tea cake cookies
directions: Mix flour, sugar, vanilla and milk.
Beat eggs and butter. Add to flour mixture.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Place remaining dough in refrigerator while batch is baking.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a buttered shallow baking dish.
Place baking dish in a pan of hot water.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: pineapple limeade
directions: Mix all ingredients except sparkling water; refrigerate until chilled.
Just before serving, stir in sparkling water.
Serve over ice.
Garnish with lime slices, if desired.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash, drain and tear spinach.
Slice water chestnuts.
Mix together; add sprouts, eggs and bacon.

title: chinese salad
directions: Put oil in wok.
Saute onions and mushrooms.
Add chicken and soy sauce.
Drain well, then mix with the macaroni.
May serve warm or cold.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix sugar, flour, spices and salt.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Spread apples over bottom of pan.
Sprinkle crumbly mixture over fruit.
Pat lightly.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: blue ribbon banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients together and put batter into two greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Place yeast in warm water (beginning with just enough of the water to dissolve yeast).
Add remaining warm water, beaten egg, margarine, sugar and flour.
Mix well.
Spoon into greased muffin pan, filling about half full.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 20 minutes or until brown.
Keep any unused mixture refrigerated.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook fettuccine to desired doneness as directed on package. Drain, rinse with hot water.
Set aside.
Meanwhile, melt margarine in 6 quart Dutch oven.
Stir in cream and pepper.
Cook over low heat about 5 minutes or until mixture thickens slightly, stirring frequently.
Stir in parmesan cheese and cook over low heat just until cheese is melted, stirring constantly. Immediately stir in cooked fettuccine; toss to coat with sauce. Stir in parsley and nutmeg.
If sauce begins to separate, stir in a little more cream and cook over low heat until smooth.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheesy potato dish
directions: Cover bottom of 13 x 9-inch dish with 2 pounds of frozen hash browns.
Sprinkle onion over top of potatoes.
Melt butter and pour half of this over potatoes.
Heat and mix cream of chicken soup, sour cream and Cheez Whiz.
Pour over potatoes.
Mix remaining butter with 2 cups crushed cornflakes and spread over casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Beat together the sour cream, 3/4 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons flour, salt, vanilla and egg. Add apples with cinnamon. Pour in pie crust. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: marshmallow nut balls
directions: Melt caramels with 2 tablespoons water over low heat.
Roll one marshmallow in caramel at a time until coated.
Roll in finely chopped nuts.

title: congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add all other ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Spray bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan with Pam.
Sprinkle nuts over bottom of pan, then add coconut.
Pour cake batter over nuts and coconut.
Mix cream cheese (room temperature), powdered sugar and melted margarine together.
Spoon mixture over top of cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Delicious warm or cold.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Sift flour, salt and sugar; cut in shortening.
Beat egg in cup.
Add vinegar, then finish filling cup with milk.
Add to flour mixture and stir with fork.
May be soupy but stir until it gets stiff.

title: nell's christmas cookies
directions: Mix well. Bake at 350° for 10 or 12 minutes.

title: fluffy fruit pie
directions: Note:
Chill Carnation evaporated milk in ice cube tray 15 to 20 minutes, or until soft ice crystals form around edge of tray.

title: coconut oatmeal pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together except coconut.
When well beaten add coconut.
Pour into 3 unbaked pie shells.
Bake in hot oven until firm.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all of these ingredients in a broiler.
Bring them to a rolling boil and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from fire and add 1/2 cup peanut butter and 3 cups uncooked oats.
Drop by tablespoon onto wax paper.

title: dottie's easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in	bottom of baking dish.	Mix 1 cup sugar with undrained peaches or leave as is if peaches are in syrup; set aside.
Mix other ingredients and pour over melted butter. Pour peaches and juice
on
top.
Bake
at
for 50 to 55 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes its own crust.

title: cross the road chicken
directions: Cook green peas with cream sauce.
Fold in diced, cooked chicken.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: peanut butter 'n' milk chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, with electric mixer on medium speed, beat spread, sugars and peanut butter until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Mix in flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in chips.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool 2 minutes; remove from cookie sheets onto wire racks to cool completely.
Serve.

title: baked turkey
directions: Preheat oven to 475° (very hot), about 9 or 10 p.m. the night before you plan your family feast.
Place turkey in a covered roaster.
Add 1 quart hot water and bake 1 hour.
Turn off oven. Do not open door.
Leave all night.
In the morning, it will be golden brown; you will have plenty of broth for dressing and gravy and the most tender turkey you ever tasted.
Be sure the roasting pan's lid fits.
I use a hot water bath canner with rack under turkey.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together shortening, eggs and bananas and add dry ingredients.
Heat until blended.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake about 1 hour in preheated 350° oven.

title: chocolate fudge ribbon cake
directions: Combine cream cheese, 1 egg and 1/4 cup sugar in a medium mixing bowl; beat at high speed until smooth.
Gradually add 3 tablespoons milk and next 3 ingredients, beating well.
Set aside.

title: linda's mop sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in a saucepan and cook over med. heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved and ingredients are completely blended.
Store in a condiment container in refrigerator.
Great used with spice rub or as a steak sauce.

title: harvard beets
directions: Cook in skillet and add the precooked diced beets.

title: rhubarb custard bars
directions: Mix ingredients with pastry blender.
Put into 9 x 13 pan. Bake for 10 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: my favorite fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges well.
Add jello to mixture.
Mix well.
Add cottage cheese and mix well.
Last, add Cool Whip and let set for an hour.
Um-um good!

title: dump cake
directions: Spray or grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Dump pineapple in and spread evenly. Dump in pie filling and spread evenly. Dump dry cake mix onto cherries and spread evenly.
Put nuts on top and then put butter slices evenly on nuts. Bake at 350° for 48 to 53 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix corn, milk and egg.
Add 1 cup crumbs, onion, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into greased 8-inch round baking dish.
Top with 1/2 cup crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: finnish oven pancakes
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Using any pans with 2-inch sides, melt butter in pans.
Pour in batter (which will be very thin).
Bake for 15 minutes or until edges are crisp, golden brown and bubbly on top.
Serve at once with syrup or jellies.
Above makes about 3 (9 x 12-inch) pans or 400 square inch of total pans.
(An 8-inch square pan has 64 square inches; a 9 x 12-inch has 108.)
This makes enough for 6 to 8 people.
It is a fun supper.

title: fudge
directions: Let sugar and milk come to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 7 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Beat until butter and chips melt.
Add nuts; pour into buttered pan.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Peel and cook zucchini; put in blender with all the other ingredients.
Blend well.
Pour in a 9-inch unbaked pie shell and bake in a 425° oven for 10 minutes, then in a 350° oven until set (about 30 to 40 minutes).
Sprinkle cinnamon on top of pie before baking, if desired.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Drain cherries, keeping 1 cup juice.
Cream shortening with 1 cup sugar, beat in eggs.
Add milk with flour and baking powder. Beat until smooth.
Pour into greased cake pan.
Mix cherries with remaining sugar and cherry juice.
Heat and pour over batter. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Eat with whipped cream or milk.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice together.
Drain and add crushed pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Add chopped pecans.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill overnight. This recipe makes 2 pies.

title: lime delight salad
directions: Boil pineapple 3 minutes.
Add jello and boil 2 minutes longer.
Let cool.
Add cottage cheese, chopped pecans and whipping cream.
Chill and serve.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Beat with mixer egg, sugar, molasses, oil, salt, soda, ginger, cloves and cinnamon.
Mix flour in with spoon.
Refrigerate until stiff.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Dip in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from oven while still puffy and light brown (otherwise, they'll be hard as rocks).
If you double the recipe, use 3 teaspoons soda.

title: chicken and ham roll-ups
directions: Place chicken between 2 sheets of waxed paper.
Flatten with flat side of knife.
Top each with 1 slice of ham.
Roll up and secure with toothpicks.
In skillet, brown roll-ups in butter. Stir in soup and water.
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes or until done.
Stir occasionally.

title: chunky pork and beans
directions: Place the beans and water in a very large kettle.
Soak overnight.	Add baking soda.
Bring to a boil and skim off the foam.
Add
remaining
ingredients,
except
parsley,
fresh chopped
onions
and
vinegar.
Bring again to a boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Partially cover and cook for 1 hour.	Remove lid and continue cooking for 45 minutes longer or until beans are tender and the mixture is very thick.
Cooking time will vary, since
the beans
vary
in
moisture,
content
and age.
Add parsley. Ladle
into
soup bowls and serve with fresh chopped onions and a little pitcher of vinegar.	Yields 6 servings.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Bring the oil and water to a full, rolling boil; add flour. Pat out in pie plate or pan.

title: old-fashioned meat loaf
directions: In large heavy skillet, cook onion, garlic, celery, carrot and scallion in butter.
Cook until carrots are tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and 1/3 cup ketchup; cook for 1 minute.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix the cocoa, sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add unbeaten egg yolks and milk; stir well.
Cook in double boiler; stir often until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and butter.
Pour into baked 9-inch pie shell.
Cover with meringue.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook and debone chicken; chop into small pieces. Chop green onions and tops. Mix with chicken, 1/2 the cheese, 2/3 of sour cream and chopped chilies. In another bowl, mix soup and remaining sour cream. Roll chicken mixture in tortillas; place in a row in large pan (9 1/2 x 13-inches).
Cover enchiladas with soup mixture and top with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted. Serves 4 to 6.

title: tuna cheese patties
directions: Add the milk to mushroom soup to make like gravy consistency. Divide gravy in 1/2, reserving 1/2 of it with egg, onion, Triscuits and pepper.
Add tuna to this mixture.
Shape into 6 patties.
Bake 20 minutes; remove from oven.
Stir together the remaining 1/2 of gravy and cheese.
Pour over hot tuna patties. Return to oven for 15 minutes.

title: red devil's food cake
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Cream the shortening and 1 cup of sugar until light. Add vanilla and egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternating with cold water, beating after each addition. Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Gradually add 3/4 cup sugar, beating until stiff peaks form. Fold into batter; blend well.
Bake in 2 greased and lightly floured 8 x 1 1/2-inch round pans at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken and rice dinner
directions: Dredge chicken pieces in flour.
In a skillet, heat oil on medium and brown chicken on all sides.
Meanwhile, combine rice, carrots, poultry seasoning, salt, pepper, milks, and water.
Pour into a greased 13 X 9 X 2 inch baking pan.
Top with chicken. Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350 degrees for 55 minutes or until rice and chicken are tender.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Brown sausage with onion; break up chunks of meat.
Remove from heat; add drained sauerkraut, cream cheese, mustard, egg, flour, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Chill; form into 1-inch balls. Flour balls; dip in egg wash. Cover with bread crumbs; chill. Deep fry in hot oil.
Brown and float in oil.
If you don't want to deep fry, brown in oven for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: old time fruit cake
directions: Mix all fruit with wine or whiskey. Let stand overnight. Mix in the a.m. all other ingredients and last add the flour. Mix with hands until it will drop from your hands. Bake in tube pan lined with brown paper that is greased well; might want to use waxed paper. Bake slowly, about 250° oven. Place a pan of water on lower rack so cake can steam for about 3 hours. Then remove pan of water. Turn heat to 300°. Let cake dry out for about 1 hour.

title: deluxe pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Mix in flour, karo syrup, sugar, margarine, vanilla, eggs, salt and nuts.
Pour into unbaked shell. bake at 400 oven 15 minutes.
Set oven to 350 and continue baking 35 - 40 minutes.
Filling should be slightly less set in center.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend oil, sugar and eggs.
Mix dry ingredients and set aside.
Add zucchini and vanilla.
Mix with oil, sugar and eggs. Add dry ingredients.
Mix all together.
Stir well.
Pour into two greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: threaded pork or beef kabobs
directions: Combine all ingredients except the meat.
Slice meat thin. Add to marinade.
Stir to coat each piece.
Put all in plastic bag and marinate overnight (24 hours is better).
Thread on skewers and barbecue over medium coals, turning occasionally, for 7 to 10 minutes or until done to your liking.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix marinade from artichoke hearts and sour cream and refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Add to other ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: tree salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill salad in refrigerator overnight before using.

title: exotic cabbage
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add onion, coconut and turmeric.
Add mustard seed.
Blend well.
Cook for 2 minutes. Add cabbage, salt and pepper; stir well.
Cook 10 minutes, covered.
Serve immediately.

title: five bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: mexican chicken chowder
directions: Put everything but the sour cream into crock-pot. Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours or 4 to 5 hours. Stir about a cup of hot soup into sour cream, then stir back into soup and let set 5 minutes.
tags: whole kernel corn with sweet peppers

title: date nut balls
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients on low.
When bubbling, cook 4 minutes.
Add next 2 ingredients, let cool a little (but its still warm).
Shape into balls and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: hot pepper relish(serves 1)
directions: Sprinkle salt over tomatoes and peppers.
Allow to stand overnight.
Drain thoroughly.
Add 1 quart vinegar and 2 quarts of water.
Boil vegetables 15 minutes; drain.
Combine 2 quarts vinegar and 4 cups sugar.
Cook until sugar is dissolved.
Add mustard seed.
Tie cloves, cinnamon, allspice and ginger root loosely in a cheesecloth bag.
Add to syrup.
Add vegetables and simmer 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Ladle into hot, sterilized jars and seal.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt peanut butter and chocolate morsels on stove.
In a large bowl, mix melted mixture with the rice chex.
Pour the contents into a large paper sack.
Add the powdered sugar and shake contents.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cream the butter and brown sugar until light, then add mashed sweet potatoes, mixing well.
Beat egg yolks with milk and stir in salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and bourbon.
In a separate bowl, beat egg whites until frothy; add about 1/4 of the beaten whites to the potato mixture, mixing well.
Gently, but thoroughly, fold in remaining whites.
Pour into partially baked pie crust and bake on center rack of oven until golden brown in a preheated 375° oven, about 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: baked fish in herb sauce
directions: Sprinkle fillets with salt and pepper.
Place in shallow baking pan.
In saucepan, combine remaining ingredients.
Bring to boiling and simmer 5 minutes.
Pour over fish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, basting occasionally.
Serves 4.

title: curry pickles
directions: Cover cucumbers and pickling salt with cold water; let stand for 7 hours in refrigerator.
Drain water.
Add vinegar, mustard and celery seed, curry powder and sugar.
Heat to a boil; pour over cucumbers.
Set on stove to get hot, but not boiling.
Then put in jars and seal.

title: mitzi's special noodles
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Melt margarine over low heat.
Add bread crumbs.
Drain noodles.
Add to browned bread crumbs, stirring constantly until all noodles are coated.
Remove from heat.
Cover.
Let stand several minutes, then serve.
Serves 3.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Combine shortening, butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well.
Add flour sifted with baking powder.
Add small amount at a time, alternating with milk.
Add vanilla and pineapple (with the juice).
Blend well.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Place in cold oven, then turn on heat to 325° and bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Pour into a greased and waxed cookie sheet.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup of chopped nuts on top and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Loosen edges of cake with knife and turn upside down on tea towel. Remove waxed paper and roll towel and cake into jelly roll.
Let cool completely.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix together ground beef, bread crumbs, salt, pepper and milk which has been heated and poured over meat mixture.
Work together and form into balls.
Make 1 layer only in baking pan.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Break 1/2 of cake in pieces and place in punch bowl.
Layer 1/2 pudding, 1/2 pineapple, 1 can cherry pie filling and 1 container of Cool Whip.
Add layer of nuts (coconut may also be added).
Repeat all layers again.
Garnish with nuts and cherries.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix together and marinate for 1 to 3 days.

title: mincemeat bars
directions: Put oats through food chopper on coarse blade.
Add flour, soda and sugar.
Mix thoroughly. Cut in shortening until mixture is crumbly. Divide into 2 parts.
Pack half firmly in oiled 7 1/2 x 11-inch pan. Spread mincemeat evenly on top, then add remaining dough and pack firmly. Bake in oven at 350° for 40 minutes. Cool good.
Cut into 14 to 16 bars.

title: mamma's peach pickle recipe
directions: Prepare fruit; let stand in lightly salted water while syrup is cooking.

Boil vinegar, sugar and spices together (spices in a loosely tied cotton bag) until mixture becomes a thick syrup. Drain salt water from peaches; add to syrup, cooking very fast until syrup covers peaches.

The syrup will not at first cover peaches, but after cooking a while, the juice comes out of the peaches and makes more syrup and also thins the first thick syrup. Keep peaches pressed down in syrup occasionally with a wooden spoon.
When done, place in hot jars and seal.
Makes about 3 to 4 jars (quarts).

title: acorn squash
directions: Halve squash lengthwise.
Scoop out seeds.
Fit squash halves together again or cover each with plastic wrap.
Microwave for 5 to 8 minutes on High.
Turn over whole squash or rotate and rearrange halves.
Microwave for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and add brown sugar, margarine and sausage in each half.
Cover with plastic wrap; microwave 5 seconds.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes. Serves 6.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together and form into a ball.
Roll in chopped pecans and refrigerate.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Cook bacon and break up into bite-size pieces.
Put a small amount of bacon grease into skillet to cook the onion.
In large pot add cooked rice, cooked bacon and onion.
Add red beans and simmer for 20 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: sausage spanish rice
directions: In a skillet, cook sausage, onion and celery or peppers over medium heat, until meat is no longer pink and vegetables are tender; drain. Add tomatoes, water, rice and chili or salsa sauce. Cover and cook over low heat for 30 minutes or until rice is tender. Remove from the heat. Sprinkle with cheese. Cover and let stand for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: jumbo gingersnaps
directions: In large bowl, measure 1/2 cup sugar and remaining ingredients.
With mixer at low speed, beat ingredients until well blended.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: applesauce-oatmeal muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease eighteen 2 1/2-inch muffin pan cups.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves in large bowl.
Combine applesauce, butter and eggs in a medium bowl.
Stir into dry ingredients until moistened.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups oats and the raisins.
Spoon batter into prepared muffin cups.
Sprinkle tops with remaining oats.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Remove from pans.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: crab-tuna fondue
directions: Drain crabmeat; flake and remove boney tissue.
Drain and flake tuna.
Combine the 2 in a small bowl.
Layer 1/3 each of the bread, seafood, cheese and parsley into a buttered 8-cup straight-sided baking dish.
Repeat to make 2 more layers.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown onions and hamburger; drain.
Add taco seasoning according to package directions.
Pat rolls into a 10-inch pie pan to form a crust.
Add meat.
Top meat with a layer of crushed Doritos.
Spread a layer of sour cream over the Doritos.
Top sour cream with grated cheese.
Add another layer of crushed Doritos. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with shredded lettuce and tomatoes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel and seed cucumbers and slice thinly (food processor works fine).
Place in colander and salt heavily.
Place plate with weight on top to press out moisture.
Allow to stand for several hours.
Rinse thoroughly and return to colander to drain, replacing plate and weight.
When as dry as possible, add remaining ingredients except for dill; chill thoroughly.
Add dill to taste just before serving.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except chips.
Pour into baking pan. Sprinkle chips on top, bake 30-40 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, spices and cornstarch.
Add egg yolks.
Gradually add sour cream.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add after baked:
Beat egg whites to hold a peak, add sugar.
When pie is baked, take out and put beaten egg on top.
Put in oven to brown.

title: dressing casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Brown onion in butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole and bake for 1 hour.

title: walnut wafers
directions: Cream together butter, brown sugar and vanilla.
Combine flour and baking powder; gradually blend into the creamed mixture.
Stir in 3/4 cup of the walnuts.
Divide dough in half.
Shape each half into a roll 8 inches long.
Roll each in the remaining walnuts. Wrap in waxed paper or plastic wrap and refrigerate several hours or freeze until firm.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Place slices 1 inch apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pizza snacks
directions: Combine olive oil, water and seasonings in a large bowl.
Add cereal and croutons, stirring evenly, until coated.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes. Stir.
Microwave an additional minute or until cereal no longer appears wet.
Sprinkle with the cheese while warm. Store in airtight containers.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook oleo, sugar, brown sugar, salt and milk on high until boiling and reduce to medium boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, Marshmallow Creme, vanilla and nuts.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
(Use wooden spoon.)

title: mini crunch
directions: Cut bagels in halves.
Spoon pizza sauce on halves of bagels. Add cheese and olives and heat in microwave or oven at 350° until cheese has melted.

title: oktoberfest sausage skillet
directions: Rinse sauerkraut.
In heavy, medium size pan, heat bacon drippings.
Add onion to saute.
Add remaining ingredients, except sausage.
Cover and cook slowly for 15 minutes or until apple slices are soft.
Add quartered sausage and continue slowly cooking, covered, until sausage is heated through.
Serves 4.

title: devil dogs
directions: Follow all directions of box.
Pour mix into greased and floured tinfoil "potato boats."
Bake for time listed for cupcakes. Turn over onto cooling rack.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Spread with Buttercream Icing.
Top with other half.
Yields 26 Devil Dogs.

title: kelly's cinnamon rolls
directions: Press 1 package of rolls into 9 x 13 pan.
Mix cream cheese, one cup of sugar and vanilla.
Spread onto bottom layer.
Place one package of rolls on top of mixture.
Melt butter.
Pour over top.
Mix together 1/2 sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle on top. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Beat with mixer until batter is blended well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 40 minutes to golden brown.

title: herbed chicken
directions: Lightly season chicken with salt and pepper.
Brown in butter in skillet. Arrange browned chicken, skin side down in 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.

title: potato candy
directions: Peel and cook potato until tender; add salt, butter and vanilla while hot.
Mash until fluffy.
Add sugar gradually, stirring with spoon until mixture can be handled - pliable, but not too stiff to roll out.

title: corned beef and noodle casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; bake in greased casserole (9 x 13-inches). Last 10 minutes, you can sprinkle 1/2 cup crushed potato chips. Bake until center looks bubbly like and brown on top. Bake in 350° oven 1 hour.

title: french bread bowl
directions: Mix as you would bread dough.
Let rise 10 minutes and punch down.
Repeat 5 times.
Form into 8 flat balls.
Let rise 10 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 30 or 35 minutes.
Cut centers out, then scoop out bread.
Fill with your favorite soup, chili or stew, then eat your bowl.

title: pasta salad
directions: Drain pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Add sugar, flour and beaten eggs to juice and cook until thick.
Cook acini de pepe and cool.
Add fruit and thickened juice and Cool Whip to the pasta. Chill and serve.

title: fried johnny cakes
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add shortening and work in gently with fingertips.
Add water gradually until a soft pliable dough is formed.
Knead gently for a few minutes, until dough is smooth.

title: sausage and bean casserole
directions: Combine beans, catsup, mustard, brown sugar and onion; place in a well-greased casserole dish.
Arrange sausages on top and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles two
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add oil; mix.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Gradually add flour mixture to the first mixture.
Mix cinnamon with 3 tablespoons sugar.
Form dough into balls, using 1 teaspoon.
Roll in cinnamon and sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes before cutting.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a bowl, combine the margarine, sweet potatoes, milk, orange juice and egg.
Mix well.
Sift the dry ingredients together and stir them into the sweet potato mixture.
Fold in the dates and nuts, mixing well.
Bake in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix soup and sour cream together.
Mix onions in.
Stir in the frozen potatoes.
Cut the cheese in little squares and place on top of the soup mixture.
Cover this mixture with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 to 45 minutes.

title: mock mack eplen pink cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and butter.
Add sugar and beat well.
Stir in egg.
Combine flour, soda and salt and add to creamed mixture. The dough will be stiff.
Add milk, vanilla and pecans.
Shape dough into balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Place on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
While cookies are hot from the oven, press down in center of each cookie with the back of a teaspoon.
Fill the center with pink frosting made with powdered sugar, vanilla and water while still hot.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: spoon yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; mix well in a large bowl all other ingredients.
Store in refrigerator and use as directed.
This will keep several days.

title: linguine with clam sauce
directions: Slowly heat oil and butter in medium skillet.
Add garlic and saute until golden brown, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Stir in clam liquid, parsley and salt; bring to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Add clams; simmer 3 minutes or until heated through.
Serve hot over linguine with garlic bread and salad.
Serves 8.

title: chili sauce
directions: Brown meat.
Add other ingredients and let simmer for a few hours.
Serve piping hot.

title: corned beef ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Form into ball and chill.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: mama's cornbread dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large mixing bowl. Pour into 11 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon surprise
directions: Boil evaporated milk for 5 minutes. Let cool, the refrigerate overnight.
Mix sugar, Jello, and
juice with boiling water.
Chill until it is setting but not stiff.
Whip milk until stiff. Beat Jello mixture until light.
Add whipped milk to Jello mixture and beat until mixed.
Chill until firm.
Makes large bowl of dessert.

title: weekend chocolate sheet cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt in large mixing bowl and mix well.
Heat water and margarine in saucepan until boiling.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix.
Beat in buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Pour batter in greased and floured 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake in 400° oven for 25 minutes.
Makes 18 servings.
Serve warm or cold with favorite topping.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Grease 2 (9 x 1 1/2-inch) layer pans.
Line bottoms with waxed paper.
Sift together dry ingredients into large bowl.
Stir in mayonnaise.
Gradually stir in water and vanilla until smooth and blended.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake in oven at 350° (moderate) for about 30 minutes or until cake springs back when touched.
Cool completely.
Remove from pans.
Frost as desired.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place half of potatoes in a well-greased 1 1/2 quart casserole. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and flour.
Dot with butter.
Repeat process.
Measure soup and add enough milk to make 2 cups.
Pour over potatoes.
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 350 degrees.
Uncover and bake 45 minutes longer.
Serves 4-6.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat all together.
Pour into homemade ice cream container and fill with milk.
Put in electric ice cream maker and add salt and snow.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: In medium bowl, mash cream cheese.
Mix dressing mix and cheddar cheese into cream cheese.
Shape the mixture into a ball. Roll the ball in the chopped nuts.
Refrigerate covered until ready to serve.

title: norm's one-pot supper
directions: Brown the beef with the onions and celery in a covered Dutch oven.
Add the peppers and cook until tender but not limp.
Add the chili sauce and stir.
Add the cheese and stir until it is melted.
Add the cooked, drained macaroni and stir.
Serve with crackers.

title: easy garden bake
directions: Grease pie plate (9 x 1 1/4-inch) or square 8 x 8-inch pan. Sprinkle zucchini, tomato, onion and cheese in pan.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into plate.

title: caramel sweet potatoes
directions: Cook sweet potatoes until tender.
Drain, cool and peel sweet potatoes.
Cut in 1/2-inch pieces crosswise and arrange in dish.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Split biscuits into 2 parts.
Wrap each eighth of apple, sprinkled with a bit of ground cinnamon, with 1/2 biscuit.
Use pan 2 1/2 to 3-inches deep and 8 to 12-inches wide.
Place the 20 dumplings into pan (separated).
Mix margarine, hot water, sugars and vanilla; pour over the dumplings.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes and enjoy a dessert better than any apple pie.

title: cowboy beans and rice
directions: In a large nonstick pan over medium heat, cook beef and onion until beef is brown.
Drain meat mixture in a colander; pat dry with paper towels.
Combine meat mixture, rice and the next 6 ingredients; stir well.
Pour mixture into a 3-quart casserole coated with cooking spray.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Stir; cover and bake an additional 30 minutes, or until rice is tender.
Yields 7 servings.
(Serving size is 1 cup.)

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour, baking soda and powder.
Blend with a whisk.
Drain fruit cocktail and set aside.

title: cheese bread
directions: Spread on French/Italian bread slices.
Broil until light brown and bubbly on top.

title: charley's favorite sweet potato pie
directions: Combine sweet potatoes with all ingredients.
Blend with electric mixer (or hand mix using a wooden spoon).
Pour into pie shell and bake in preheated 400° oven about 30 minutes, or until golden brown and puffy.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Sprinkle with dry powdered mustard and cover with strips of bacon.
Bake in hot oven.

title: simple hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and cooked macaroni and remaining ingredients. Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: sweet and sour green beans
directions: Cut bacon into 1/2-inch pieces.
Fry until crisp; drain. Saute onions in bacon grease until brown.
Drain beans.
Add liquid to onions.
Cook until reduced to 1/2 cup.
Add remaining ingredients and beans.
Add bacon when ready to serve.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients in given order.
Pour in greased and floured stem pan.
Place in cold oven.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: black bean salad
directions: Mix beans, corn and onion; set aside.
Mix olive oil, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over bean mixture; refrigerate.
Just before serving, add 1 package feta cheese.
Serve with large corn chips.

title: sausage surprise
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients and put in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix eggs, milk and dry mustard well.
Pour over top of casserole.
Let it set overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain canned salmon, saving liquid.
Remove bones and make white sauce by blending butter or margarine over low heat with flour and liquid.
Add egg, salmon and seasonings.
Butter 2 slices of bread and cube.
Put salmon in a greased pan; add cubed bread and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Season baked sweet potatoes with salt and milk.
Mash up good. Form into balls.
Press a pitted prune which has been soaked. The prune should not be visible.
Dip the balls in bread crumbs and egg.
Brown the balls in deep fat.
Serve at once.

title: fresh apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare apples.
Combine dry ingredients; mix with apples to coat.
Put into pastry lined 9-inch pie pan. Drizzle with Wesson oil.
Cover with top crust and cut slits for steam to escape.
Make high-fluted rim.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes, until nicely browned and juice begins to bubble through slits in crust.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: beef casserole
directions: Place beef in casserole; salt and pepper. Add soup and bread. Put onion slices on top; cover. Bake at 300° for 3 hours or until tender. Add mushrooms. Serves 4. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: chicken stew
directions: Cut chicken into strips.
Brown chicken in a skillet full of oil.
Then add chicken into a saucepan of water.
Brown pepper, onion and green onion in oil.
Then add to chicken and water.
Add cream of chicken soup.
Simmer until done.
If not thick enough, add cornstarch.
Serve over rice.

title: broccoli salad(serves 4 to 6)
directions: The night before make sauce.
Mix together vinegar, sugar and mayonnaise.
Refrigerate overnight.
Add together broccoli, nuts, bacon and onion in a bowl.
Mix in sauce.
Chill before serving.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, shortening and pumpkin.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Mix into pumpkin mixture.
Add vanilla, nuts and raisins.
Stir well.
Bake at 375° until browned.

title: mississippi baked turkey
directions: Preheat oven to 475°, about 9:00 p.m. or 10:00 p.m. the night before you plan to serve your turkey.
Place turkey in a covered roaster with the onion, apple and celery.
Add 1 quart warm water. Bake one hour, turn off oven.
Do not open oven door.
Leave turkey in oven all night.

title: picante cream cheese dip
directions: Mix well in mixer. Serve with chips. Easy and great.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Layer with coconut (frozen is best) and pecans.
Mix German chocolate cake mix per directions on box and pour over coconut and pecans.
Melt butter and cream cheese in microwave.
Add powdered sugar and spoon over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: spinach pie (cottage cheese)(spanakopita)
directions: Clean and chop spinach; place in large mixing bowl.
Add Feta cheese, cottage cheese and seasonings.
Add egg yolks; mix thoroughly.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into spinach mixture.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan; place 6 pastry sheets into pan, brushing each with melted butter.
Spread spinach mixture evenly ; cover with 6 individually buttered pastry sheets.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until golden brown.
Cut into squares; serve hot or cold.

title: no crust pecan pie
directions: Stir all ingredients into unbeaten egg whites.
Mix well. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: aunt anne's beef burgundy
directions: Brown stew beef in a large Dutch oven.
Gradually add soups, Burgundy and bay leaves.
Place in a 350° oven, uncovered, for 3 1/2 hours.
The last 15 minutes, add water chestnuts and mushrooms.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix well together and spread on serving plate.
Spread shrimp sauce over top.
Refrigerate and serve with crackers.
Very good!

title: crab cakes
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and saute onion and bread crumbs over medium heat for 2 to 3 minutes. Combine with all ingredients except oil and flour; chill for at least 2 hours. Shape into 8 cakes, dust with flour. Fry cakes in oil for about 8 minutes over medium heat until brown, turn once.

title: chicken oriental
directions: Stir
the
first
5 ingredients in a bowl until smooth; set aside.
Place
tablespoon oil in pan;
cook vegetables and garlic on high heat 3 to 5 minutes, until crispy.
Remove. Heat remaining
tablespoon
oil
in skillet.	Add chicken; stir-fry 4 minutes.	Add vegetables and cornstarch mixture to skillet; bring to boil for 1 minute.
Makes 4 servings.

title: healthy walnut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan with oil. Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar; set aside.
In second bowl, beat egg until thick.
Add milk; continue beating until blended.
Add dry ingredients and nuts; stir until mixture is moist.
Turn mixture into pan.
Bake for 40 minutes, or until tester comes out clean.
Loosen loaf from sides of pan.
Turn out, right side up, on wire rack to cool.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In a medium saucepan, stir together the brown sugar, cornstarch and chili powder.

Stir in the tomato sauce, vinegar, catsup and corn syrup. Add 1/2 cup water. Bring to a boil. Lower heat to low and cook, uncovered, for 30 minutes. Stir in orange juice. Simmer 5 minutes more. Baste sauce on meat or poultry the last quarter of grilling or broiling time. Reheat sauce and pass it to use on individual servings.

title: 15 bean soup
directions: Cut meat from ham bone and reserve.
Place ham bone in big stock pot with water.
Simmer 4 hours or overnight.
Remove bone and skim fat.
Add beans and all other ingredients.
Simmer for 2 hours covered.
Add Tabasco, salt and pepper to taste.

title: ultimate cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients with 1/2 of corned beef and form into ball.
Roll ball into remaining corned beef.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Mix crumbs, cheese, parsley, garlic, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken into melted margarine, then into crumbs.
Lay chicken in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Chicken will be juicy and no longer pink inside.

title: taco sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender on low speed for 10 seconds, then pour into a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat immediately.
Cool, pour into a bottle, seal and store in refrigerator.
Makes 1 quart.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Mix strawberries, jello and sugar in a saucepan.
Heat until sugar and jello dissolve.
Cool.
Mix pudding, sour cream, milk and Cool Whip.

title: green tomato bread
directions: Stir together eggs, oil, sugar, vanilla and green tomato.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour batter into two well oiled loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: orange delight
directions: Bring pudding, jello and water to a rolling boil.
Cool.
Add Cool Whip and oranges.
Pour into mold and refrigerate.

title: pizza crust
directions: Place flour and salt in large mixing bowl.
Put yeast and sugar in warm water and wait until it gets frothy.
Add oil.
Then pour over flour and mix until sticky.
Add more flour, if needed, to make dough stiff.
Let raise for 1 to 2 hours.
Roll out or knead out.
Makes 2 large pizzas.

title: sunshine cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together for 3 minutes.
Bake in 3 layers for 25 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool completely.

title: wedding punch
directions: Make ice ring of punch Kool-Aid to use in the punch.

title: fanny farmer's fudge
directions: Boil sugar and milk for 10 minutes; take off heat.
Add chocolate chips and butter; beat until smooth.
Add 1 cup nuts. Put into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: copper pennies(marinated carrots)
directions: Cook sliced carrots and drain.
Mix soup and other ingredients.
Pour over carrots.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together all fruits.
Add dry pudding mix and the Tang (dry).
Mix well and store in refrigerator.

title: polynesian vegetables
directions: Cut peppers into 1-inch chunks.
Cut onion and tomatoes into 1/2-inch wedges.
Combine
preserves, soy sauce, vinegar, ginger, garlic powder and salt.
Add peppers and onion.
Cover and cook for 10 minutes
or	until vegetables are tender.
Add tomatoes and pineapple.	Heat thoroughly and serve.

title: christmas corn
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Combine all ingredients together well.
Pour into crust. Refrigerate overnight for best results.
Top with blackberries.

title: canned fruit punch
directions: Combine fruit juices.
Chill.
Before serving, pour over ice cubes.
Add chilled ginger ale.
Size of serving:
4 ounces. Serves 50 people.

title: coon dogs (appetizers)
directions: Let sausage come to room temperature.
Mix dry Bisquick and sausage with hands.
Melt cheese in double boiler; add Tabasco sauce.
Add cheese to sausage mixture; mix well.
Shape into teaspoon-sized balls.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes. (May be made ahead of time and frozen, then baked without thawing.)
Serve hot.

title: tiny orange muffins
directions: Combine butter and sugar.
Add eggs and milk.
Add dry ingredients.
Add orange rind and raisins; stir until moistened. Bake 15 minutes in 400° oven in small greased tins.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries (a blender can also be used).
Cover with sugar and let stand.
Prepare gelatin.
Put in refrigerator until partly congealed.
Remove.
Mix in remaining ingredients and return to refrigerator until firmly congealed.

title: tender barbecued chicken
directions: Place chicken in slow cooker.
Top with onion and lemon slices.
Combine barbecue sauce and cola and pour over all.
Cover and cook on low for 8-10 hours until chicken juices run clear.

title: many fruited punch
directions: Combine fruit juices and cold water.
Add ginger ale and club soda just before serving.
Float ice ring.
Yields 40 servings.

title: roll out cookie dough
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream butter and sugar with electric mixer.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add baking powder and flour, one cup at a time.
The dough will not be very stiff.
Blend last in by hand.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: In a large bowl, combine turkey, sour cream, soups, mushrooms, celery and garlic powder.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, put spaghetti and contents of bowl, mixing well.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: old fashioned blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 12-cup muffin pan.
In medium bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Mix well with pastry blender.
Cut in margarine and shortening until it makes fine crumbs.

title: beef stew
directions: Add enough water to tomato juice to make 2 cups liquid.
Bake covered at 250° for 4 to 5 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: In a frying pan melt the butter; add the mushrooms (if fresh). Cut up the chicken and put them in the butter.
Cook the chicken until all sides are cooked.
(I remove the chicken for the next part, but not necessary.)
Add the sour cream and a taste of vermouth or cooking wine.
Add in the chicken (and the canned mushrooms); lower the heat and cover.
Cook for about 20 minutes or until the chicken is completely cooked.
Serve on a bed of rice.

title: light and easy waffles
directions: Mix all together; pour into waffle iron.
Make whole thing into waffles.
Very light and airy.
Can be reheated in toaster after refrigerated if not all eaten.

title: potato salad
directions: Cut potatoes and eggs up.
Put in onion.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and mustard together.
Pour the mayonnaise, vinegar and mustard on the potatoes, eggs and onion; mix well.
Eat while it's still warm.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed, only drier.
Rinse and drain crab and shrimp.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease 4 quart casserole. Combine all ingredients in casserole.
Stir to mix well.
Bake uncovered 1 hour at 325°.
Can be made day ahead.
Serves 12.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Boil this all together and let it cool. Flavor with lemon and make it as you would a custard pie.

title: chicken breasts in sour cream
directions: Mix soup and sour cream together.
Spread over chicken.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: creamy baked fillets
directions: Place fillets in a lightly greased 9-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with pepper and dot with butter.
Spoon soup over fillets; sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake uncovered at 350° for about 20 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork. Serves 4.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and mix well.
Cook 15 minutes at 400°.

title: mom's best chili
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients in a Dutch oven over medium-high heat, stirring until beef crumbles and is no longer pink; drain. Add beans and remaining ingredients.
Bring mixture to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for at least 1 1/2 hours.
Ladle into individual bowls and top with shredded cheese if desired.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chocolate heaven
directions: 1st Layer:
Melt margarine.
In a medium bowl combine margarine, flour, and 2 cups of nuts until well mixed.
Spread into a baking pan.
Bake in oven for 20 minutes (or until crust is golden brown) at 350°.
Let cool completely.

title: salsa
directions: Bring tomatoes, onion and peppers to a boil. Simmer 45 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: amaretto chicken
directions: Mix the can of frozen orange juice with a half can of water Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Combine flour, salt, pepper, paprika, and garlic salt.
Coat chicken with this mixture.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Combine butter and sugar; stir in eggs.
Add soda to buttermilk and add alternately with flour.
Add orange slices, coconut, dates, nuts and orange rind.
Turn into 10-inch greased tube pan.
Bake 2 hours in 300° oven.
Allow to cool in pan overnight, setting on a cooling rack.
This 5-pound cake should be mixed by hand as beaters will make it light and fruit will go to the bottom.

title: florida stuffed peppers
directions: Cook rice in 1
cups boiling water for 15 minutes. Cut a thin slice
from
top
of
peppers;
remove seeds.
Drop peppers into boiling water
for 3 minutes only.
Drain and set upright in baking dish.

title: v-8 juice stew
directions: May cook for about 2 hours on top of stove or 6 hours on low in crock-pot.

title: lemon lush
directions: Make in glass 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine flour, butter and nuts in baking dish.
Pat to cover bottom and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Beat Cool Whip, cream cheese and 10x sugar.
Spread over baked layer.
Beat pudding and milk until thick.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Cover with Cool Whip.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Drain all vegetables well.
Marinate at least 24 hours in mixture of sugar, water, oil and vinegar.
Stir occasionally while marinating.

title: fruitcake squares
directions: Melt butter in 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan. Sprinkle on crumbs (top and sides of pan to distribute crumbs evenly).
Sprinkle on coconut.
Distribute candied fruit as even as possible over coconut.
Cut dates into small amount of flour so they won't stick together.
Distribute dates over fruit.
Sprinkle on nuts.
Press mixture lightly with hands to level it in pan. Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over top.

title: rosy pickled eggs
directions: In a large bowl, combine beet juice, vinegar, 4 cups water, garlic, bay leaf, pickling spices and salt.
Mix well. Cover and refrigerate for several days. Makes 12 pickled eggs.

title: strawberry pecan cake
directions: In bowl combine cake mix, jello,

oil and milk. Beat until well blended. Add eggs, nuts and 1/2 pkg. of strawberries. Beat on high until foamy. Pour batter into 3- 8 inch cake pans or 2- 9 inch pans. Bake at 350° until done. For 8 inch pans check at 15 minutes for 9 inch pans check at 20 minutes. Takes only 20 or 30 minutes to cook.

title: old-fashioned gingerbread
directions: Sift flour and soda together.
Stir all ingredients together. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° oven about 30 minutes.
Nice when topped with whipped cream.

title: mini meatballs
directions: Heat sauce in microwave until hot and blended. Spoon sauce over meatballs. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients dry.
Put water in pan; add dry ingredients.
Bring to a rolling boil, stirring for 1 minute. Cool.
Add Cool Whip and fruit.

title: fish chowder
directions: In a large pot (heavy, so chowder will not stick), cook bacon until crispy.
Add onions and saute until tender.
Add potatoes, water, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer until potatoes are tender, but firm.
Add frozen or fresh fish fillets (can be cut into large chunks); cook covered 8 to 10 minutes.
Stir until fish breaks up easily.
Stir in corn and milk. Cook covered until heated thoroughly.
Add butter.

title: french rice
directions: Combine soup and butter; stir well.
Drain mushrooms and water chestnuts, reserving liquids.
Add enough water to reserved liquid to make 1 1/3 cups.
Add mushrooms, water chestnuts, liquid and rice to soup; stir well.
Pour into lightly greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot chocolate
directions: *For thicker chocolate, include in the milk 1 can evaporated milk.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water until frothy.
Add nuts and mix lightly.
Combine sugar, salt and cinnamon and toss with nuts.
Mix thoroughly and spread evenly on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 225° for 1 hour; turn occasionally.
Cool.
Keep in airtight container.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift together corn meal, flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and sugar. Place in a small bowl. Add onions, buttermilk and water. Mix well. Add butter or margarine and egg. Blend. Drop by small tablespoons into preheated deep fat (370°). Cook until golden brown. Yield: about 30.

title: veal barbecue
directions: Cook veal.
Make barbecue sauce while meat cools.
In a skillet, brown onion and celery with salad oil.
Cook until tender.
Add 1/2 cup catsup, 1/3 cup water, 2 tablespoons lemon juice and 1 tablespoon each of brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar and mustard.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add meat.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling water until tender.
Drain.
Arrange stalks in greased 11 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Place chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder. Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: it's better than potato salad
directions: Cook rice; transfer to bowl and chill.
Add mayonnaise, celery, onion, mustard and salt to chilled rice.
Mix well. Cover and chill.
Stir in remaining ingredients before serving.

title: garlic dijon dressing
directions: Shake together and store.
Yield: 3/4 cup.
Double or triple as needed.

title: sweet chicken
directions: Mix and coat chicken.
Bake uncovered 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Coat skillet with cooking spray.
Saute onion and garlic for 2 minutes.
Add chicken, parsley, oregano, basil, salt, pepper and tomatoes.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Mix egg and milk.
Add the 2 mixtures together.
Add butter and pineapple.
Cook in a double boiler until thick.
Pour into a baked pie shell.
Add meringue of 2 egg whites and sugar.
Brown in oven.

title: yeast breads
directions: Combine 6 cups flour, sugar and yeast in bowl.
Mix condensed milk and oil with enough warm water to measure 4 cups.
Mix well. Add to flour mixture, mix well.
Add remaining 2 cups flour, mix well.
Place in greased bowl.
Let rise in warm place for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until double in bulk.
Knead on floured surface until smooth, adding additional flour if needed.
Divide into 4 portions.
Place in 4 greased 3 x 7-inch loaf pans.
Let rise for 40 minutes.
Bake in 350° oven until bread tests done.

title: best chocolate fudge sauce for ice cream
directions: Melt first 2 ingredients over low heat.
Add alternately the sugar and milk (1 can).
Blend well after each addition.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir about 7 or 8 minutes until thick and creamy.
Remove from heat and stir in the vanilla.
Cool.
Pour into a jar.
This sauce will keep a long time in the refrigerator.

title: strawberry cream cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, strawberries, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon in crust and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cherry devilicious cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions, baked in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Cool.

title: orange pecan thumbprints(no bake cookies)
directions: Place crushed wafers in medium size bowl.
Combine corn syrup and liqueur in a small bowl; drizzle over wafers.
Mix together with hands until well blended.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground chuck, drain and add water and taco seasoning mix. Simmer for 5 minutes; set aside to cool.

title: rice pudding
directions: Scald milk.
Add sweetener and mix well.
Add rice, nutmeg, vanilla and salt and stir.
Pour into a lightly greased baking dish and bake in a 300° oven for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Stir several times during first 1 1/2 hours of baking.
Cool before serving. Makes 5 servings, 75 calories per serving.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat softened cream cheese and condensed milk together.
Beat in lime juice.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour into shell.
Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.

title: sticky buns
directions: The night before, spray Pam on bottom and sides of a 10 x 13-inch pan.
Lay frozen rolls evenly on bottom of pan.
Sprinkle pudding mix and brown sugar on top of rolls.
Dot with pieces of butter.
Leave on counter overnight to raise.
In the morning, heat oven to 350° and bake for 25 minutes.
Pull apart and enjoy. Feeds 12 people (3 each).

title: pig licking cake
directions: Mix the above ingredients for 3 minutes.
Pour into 3 cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Heat pie filling in sauce pan. Add jello and stir until it is dissolved. Add cold coke and nuts. Refrigerate until set.

title: basic marinara sauce
directions: Saute onion in a mixture of the olive oil and garlic until tender.
Add remaining ingredients, cover and cook 15 minutes over medium heat.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serve over hot cooked pasta.
Makes 3 cups.

title: congo bars
directions: Cream the brown sugar, oleo, eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Add chips and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: quick spanish rice
directions: In a saucepan, combine first seven ingredients. Cook rice and drain.
Simmer other ingredients 10 minutes.
Add cooked rice. Stir to mix.
Garnish with green onion and serve.

title: french onion soup
directions: Heat butter and oil in 9 to 10 quart pan.
Saute onions until golden brown.
Add garlic, salt, m.s.g, Maggi, Tabasco, Dijon mustard, wine and consomme.
Bring to boil, stirring well.
Simmer 2 to 3 hours.
Add 1 teaspoon brandy at time of serving to each bowl.
Top soup in bowl with slice of rye bread or croutons.
