Cover with slice of Swiss cheese and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: black walnut cookies
directions: Cream the butter.
Add sugar and beaten eggs. Sift flour, soda and cream of tartar together. Add and mix thoroughly.
Add chopped nuts.
Chill.
Form into a roll and slice.
Bake on buttered cookie sheet until lightly browned at about 375°.

title: tuna tofu salad
directions: Cut tofu into 1/2-inch cubes and place in serving dish.
Layer tuna, tomatoes and green onions on top of tofu cubes.
Combine shoyu, lemon juice, salad oil and sesame oil.
Pour over salad. Serve immediately.

title: mandarin orange salad mold
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add juice from oranges.
Stir in sherbet and orange sections.
Chill until set.

title: beef and pea pod stir-fry
directions: Partially freeze beef.
Thinly slice meat across the grain into bite size strips.
In a 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe casserole, cook meat strips, covered, on 100% power (High) for 4 to 6 minutes or until meat is brown, stirring every 2 minutes.
Use a slotted spoon to remove meat from the dish, reserving juices.
Set meat aside.

title: berried delight
directions: Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and melted butter. Press firmly into bottom of a 13 x 9 pan. Chill. Beat cream cheese with 1/4 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons milk until smooth. Fold in half of the whipped topping. Spread over crust. Arrange strawberries in even layer.

title: california chili
directions: Use a 2-quart pan to cook beans, covered with water, for 1 hour.
Add water, if necessary, until beans are tender.
In heavy kettle, saute onions, green pepper and garlic in oil until onions are transparent.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, covered, 1 hour.
Uncover and cook 1/2 hour longer, until thick.
May be frozen and reheated.

title: german steak rolls
directions: Roll steaks real thin.
Spread a thin layer of mustard on them. Add a slice of ham and 1 quarter dill pickle.
Roll each steak and fasten with toothpick.
Dredge in seasoned flour.
Brown in small amount of hot oil.
Place single layer of steak rolls in baking pan.
Put some of seasoned flour in oil and make a thin water gravy.
Pour over steaks, enough to cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: gingerbread cupcakes
directions: Combine whole wheat flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.

Heat margarine and molasses until melted. Combine buttermilk or sour milk (1/2 cup milk plus 3/4 tablespoon lemon juice or 1/2 tablespoon vinegar; let stand for a few minutes) with baking soda and egg.
Add molasses mixture to the flour mixture; stir.
Add egg-milk mixture; stir until combined.
Do not overstir.
Place in lined muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes, or place in a greased 9 x 9-inch pan and bake for 18 to 20 minutes.
May be eaten as is or frosted with cream cheese frosting.

title: chocolate cream cheese frosting
directions: Combine cream cheese and milk.
Gradually add sugar, blending thoroughly after each addition.
Add melted chocolate, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Spread on cake.
Enough to frost a 2-layer, 8-inch cake.

title: amish slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and onions fine.
Add sugar and let stand.

title: cottage cheese patties
directions: Saute onions in oil and set aside.
Add eggs, seasonings, cottage cheese and bread crumbs.
Blend.
Form into patties.
Fry in hot oil until brown.

title: drain cleaner
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a bowl and store covered.
To use, spoon 1/4 cup of the mixture into the drain, the mixture will bubble.
When bubbling has stopped, run water down the drain.
Use the mixture once a month to keep your drains clear and clean.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, dry mustard and onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix all together until well blended.
Pour into a greased 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour, stirring once.

title: green bean and corn casserole
directions: Mix beans, corn, onion, bell pepper, sour cream and cheese. Add salt and pepper.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Top with cracker crumbs and melted butter and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tropical chicken salad
directions: Place chicken and celery in a large bowl.
Combine mayonnaise and curry powder, add to chicken mixture and mix well.
Cover and chill for at least 30 minutes.
Before serving, add the bananas, oranges, and coconut, toss gently.
Serve on salad greens. Sprinkle with nuts.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together in a large bowl. Form into small balls. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: ham and cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients, except pecans, and form into a ball.
Roll in pecans to cover.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until fluffy; add next 4 ingredients.
Sprinkle pecans on bottom of pie shell.
Pour the filling over pecans.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake 35 minutes longer.

title: spice cake
directions: Place shortening into pan; add sugar, water, salt and spices and boil 3 minutes.
Cool and add flour, baking powder and soda. Mix well and put into a well-greased cake pan and bake in oven (275°) for 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter.
Add tomatoes, mushrooms, olives and oregano.
Add ground beef and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Place 1/2 spaghetti in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 1/2 vegetable mixture.
Sprinkle with 1 cup Cheddar cheese.
Repeat layers.
Mix water and soup until smooth; pour over.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until heated through.

title: shrimp curry crepe filling
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Rinse cooked rice under cold water; drain thoroughly and pat dry with paper towels.
Put rice in casserole bowl and mix with vegetables.
Cover casserole and place in center of the oven and bake 35 minutes.
After 35 minutes, check to see if all water has been absorbed.
If not, replace lid and cook a further 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and add butter, stirring with a wooden spoon, until butter is melted.
Serve hot.

title: nan's icebox cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add in and mix the egg (beaten) and molasses.
Mix in flour, salt and baking soda.
Fold in pecans. Make several rolls and refrigerate for several hours or overnight. Slice and bake until lightly browned at 350°.

title: snickerdoodles cookies
directions: Beat shortening, sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Stir dry mixture into top 3 ingredients.
Shape into balls (about size of walnut). Roll balls in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Press balls down with a fork and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: squash dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole.
Bake 30 or 40 minutes at 400°.

title: cracker jack popcorn
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add last 3 ingredients, pour over 6 qts. popped popcorn, place on cookie sheet and bake 1 hour at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix ingredients; heat salad oil to 400° in electric skillet. Drop batter by tablespoon into hot fat.
Fry until browned.
Turn once.

title: lemon rub pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into an unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes (knife comes out clean when inserted close to center of pie). Very tart. Great after a fried fish dinner.

title: onion and tomato soup
directions: Combine ingredients in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil and simmer for about 30 minutes or until onions are soft.
Serve garnished with 1/2 egg (hard-boiled) and toast triangles on the side.

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers very thin.
Crisp with ice cubes. Combine sour cream, lemon juice, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Dry cucumbers and fold in dressing.
Serves 4.

title: raspberry bavarian pie(wonderful hot weather dessert)
directions: Combine raspberries with a cup of water.
Heat to boiling, crushing berries with a spoon to extract juice.
Strain and measure the juice.
Add enough water to make 3 cups of liquid. Pour over the gelatin and stir until gelatin dissolves.
Chill until thickened.
If gelatin mixture becomes too hard, microwave it for 10 seconds on Full power, until softened.
Beat with rotary beater until foamy.
Gently fold in whipped cream into gelatin mixture and turn into crust and chill until firm.
Serves 6.

title: raisin bars
directions: Mix first four ingredients and boil 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
This mixture sticks easily so it needs to be cooked on low heat.
Remove from heat and add raisins and coconut. Mixture may be poured on a layer of graham crackers in a pan and then topped with another layer of crackers.
Pull apart when cold. You may also let mixture cool and spread on crackers like a sandwich.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: mom's yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water. Sift flour, soda, baking powder, salt and sugar. Add shortening to dry ingredients, blending with pastry blender. Add buttermilk (at room temperature) with yeast mixture to dry ingredients. Mix together and use immediately or store until ready for use. May be cut and covered and kept in the refrigerator for 7 to 10 days. Be sure to roll out on floured surface. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400° to 425°.

title: carrot pineapple cake
directions: Put 2 cups grated carrots, 2 cups sugar and 1 1/2 cups vegetable oil in a large bowl.
Beat well.
Add 4 eggs, one at a time.
Sift 2 cups flour with 2 teaspoons soda, 1 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Add to mixture.
Add 1 small can crushed pineapple with juice.
Bake in 3 layer pans, greased and lined with wax paper, then greased and floured.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 35 minutes.

title: crescent cordon bleu
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 large cookie sheets.
In a medium bowl, combine chicken, ham, mushrooms and cheese.
Separate crescent roll dough into 12 rectangles.
Firmly press perforations to seal. Spoon rounded 1/2 cupful of chicken mixture onto center of each rectangle.
Pull 4 corners of dough to center. Crimp edges to seal.
Place on prepared cookie sheets.
Brush with beaten egg. Bake at 350° for 14 to 15 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 12 servings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into an 11 x 7 x 2-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, melt butter over low heat.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper until smooth.
Stir in milk and cook, stirring constantly, for about 10 minutes or until thickened. Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups of cheese until melted.
Mix macaroni and sauce together and pour in buttered baking dish. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until cheese is melted well on top.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cherry cake
directions: Beat together until well blended.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: neptune salad
directions: Dice crab meat in a salad bowl.
Dice celery.
Combine mayonnaise, milk, salt and pepper.
Blend, making a sauce.
Mix with meat, celery and mushrooms.
Chill.

title: delicious dip
directions: Heat soup
over
medium heat.
Add gelatine, then cream cheese broken
in chunks (cheese remains sort of chunky).	Add celery, onion
and	drained
meat.	Remove	from heat; stir in mayo. Place in mold sprayed with Pam.
May be made day ahead.

title: pineapple fluffy
directions: Mix jello according to package.
Add pineapple and mix well. Add Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Stir well.
Refrigerate.

title: christmas strawberries
directions: Mix almonds, Eagle Brand, jello, coconut and vanilla. Form into strawberry shape. Roll in red sugar. Roll top in green sugar.

title: apple cake
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Put sugar on apples; add oil, eggs, vanilla and stir.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Bake 1 hour at 350 degrees in 9 x 13 inch pan.
Cool and ice.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer ingredients in order as listed in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: snowballs
directions: Heat your oven to 400 degrees.
Mix butter, 1/2 cup of powdered sugar & vanilla. Mix in flour, salt and nuts until dough holds together.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain cans of beans.
Chop onion and pepper.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Warm oil, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over vegetables.
Set in refrigerator 2 hours before serving.

title: rice pot jambalaya
directions: Mix all ingredients in an 8 c. rice pot and turn pot on. Very easy to cook. Good with green salad and french bread.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together and pour in casserole baking dish.
Sprinkle crushed corn flakes, if desired, on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: sauteed vegetables and sausage dish
directions: Saute first four ingredients in butter.
Saute sausage and add to vegetables.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve over rice.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix well.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: blender pot de creme
directions: Put chocolate bits in blender and pour over them the scalded milk.
Add egg yolks and flavoring.
Pour into demitasse cups. Chill at least 2 hours.
Top with whipping cream (or Cool Whip). Serves 10.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: In a small bowl, beat eggs well. In a large bowl, cream together cream cheese, margarine, butter, salt and sugar until smooth, gradually adding cake flour alternatively with eggs. Then add flavoring. DO NOT PREHEAT OVEN. Bake in an ungreased tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°. DO NOT OPEN OVEN DURING BAKING TO LOOK.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together very well using hands, if desired.
Shape into ball; chill.
Roll in pecans.

title: squash chips
directions: Peel and seed squash.
Slice tissue paper thin as for potato chips.
Soak in ice water for 1 hour.
Drain and pat dry.
Fry in deep hot fat (360°) until brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with salt and ginger.

title: salisbury steak
directions: In bowl, combine beef, bread crumbs, egg and 2 tablespoons of the onion and salt.
Shape into 4 oval patties.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Bake cake at 350 in a greased and floured pan for 30 to 40 minutes.
Put icing on cake while cake is still warm.

title: italian bread salad
directions: Cut bread into 1-inch cubes.
Heat 6 tablespoons of oil in large frypan.
Add garlic and bread; cook until bread is golden on all sides, about 10 minutes.
Remove to a bowl.

title: pork chop supper
directions: In skillet, over medium heat, melt butter.
Brown chops for three minutes, each side.
Add potatoes, carrots and onions. Combine soup and water, pour over the top.
Cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding a little milk, if necessary.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Freezes well.

title: homestyle hash browns
directions: Heat oil and butter at medium heat.
Grate potatoes and add to oil.
Sprinkle onions on top.
Saute a few minutes, then flip to cook other side.
Season with salt and pepper.
Very good with country breakfast.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: sweet and sour beef stew
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add
and cook until tender over low heat brown
sugar,
carrots,
vinegar,
onions, Worcestershire sauce, tomato sauce and 1/2 cup water.
Combine cornstarch and 1/4 cup water and add to thicken.
Serve over rice, noodles or baked potatoes.
Serves 6.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cover carrots with chicken broth or water (I use chicken broth).
Cook, uncovered, until tender, about 3 to 5 minutes. Drain.

title: upside down cake
directions: Melt butter in a 8 x 8 x 2 inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Cover with pie filling.
Pour cake batter over all. Bake at 350 degree oven for 45 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes, invert on a serving plate.

title: quick crab soup
directions: Combine, heat and serve.
Quick and delicious.

title: german baked pork and beans
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake at 325° in a 3-quart casserole, uncovered, for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: party mix
directions: Melt margarine in preheated 250° oven.
Stir in seasonings. Gradually add cereals, nuts and pretzels; stir to coat evenly. Bake 1 hour; stirring every 15 minutes.
Spread on paper towels to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: velveeta dip
directions: Melt cheese in saucepan and add tomatoes.
Serve with nachos.

title: angel food cake
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until foamy.
Add cream of tartar. Beat until stands in peaks.
Fold in rest of ingredients.
Bake for 35 minutes at 375°.

title: psomi bread(greek)
directions: Heat milk; stir in butter, salt and sugar.
Soften yeast in warm water.
Sift flour in a large bowl.
Make a well in flour and add yeast and water.
Gradually add warm milk.
Knead until smooth.
Place in greased bowl, cover and let rise until doubled. Knead again and form into rolls or loaves.
Place on greased pan, brush with melted butter and let rise for 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes for loaves or 30 minutes for rolls.
Makes 2 loaves or about 4 dozen rolls.

title: buttermilk waffles
directions: Beat eggs light, add milk, flour sifted with cornmeal, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Melt lard and butter, add with soda dissolved in warm water.
Mix carefully and bake on well-greased waffle iron.
Serve hot with butter and syrup.
Sufficient for sixteen individual waffles.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant in small amount of water; drain and mash.
Add salt and pepper to taste and mix with all ingredients, except margarine, cracker crumbs and cheese.
Place in casserole dish. Cover with cheese and cracker crumbs.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch casserole dish with margarine.
Brown sausage and sprinkle over bread.
Mix eggs with milk and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over sausage.
Sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can make up and freeze for later use.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut all biscuits into 4 pieces and roll in mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Put into a Bundt pan.
Mix and melt together the butter, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Make two (8-inch) layers. Split both layers horizontally after cooled.
Blend together the sugar, sour cream and coconut until chilled.
Cream mixtures between cake layers.
Blend remaining cup with Cool Whip and spread over top and sides of cake.
Seal in airtight container. Keep in icebox 24 hours before serving.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients, then save 1 1/2 cups to sprinkle on top before baking.
Add rest of ingredients to balance of mix.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 1 hour.

title: spaghetti with 4 onions
directions: Heat oil over low heat.
Add red, yellow and green onions and shallots.
Cook for 15 minutes or until onions are golden.
Add garlic; cook 2 more minutes.
Stir in apple juice; cook for 1 minute.

title: stir-fried bean sprouts
directions: Heat oil in wok.
Cook onion for 2 minutes, then add beans and stir-fry for 1 minute.
Add water, soy sauce, lemon juice and season to taste.
Cook for 5 minutes, tossing beans in the liquid until it has evaporated.
Add mushrooms and cook till tender.
Add bean sprouts and fry for 2 minutes.
Serve at once with roasted or broiled meat.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and melted margarine.
Press firmly into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese with 1/4 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons milk until smooth.
Fold in half of Cool Whip and spread over crust.
Prepare pudding with 2 1/2 cups milk and pour over cream cheese mixture. Chill and top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: stuffed potatoes with crabmeat
directions: Put potatoes in oven at 450° for approximately 1 hour or until done.
When done, take a knife and cut a round circle on the potato and scoop out the inside; save the shells.
Mix potatoes, butter, salt, pepper and half and half in large mixing bowl (add the half and half, a little at a time, until it has the consistency of mashed potatoes).
Next, stir in the green onions and crabmeat.
Place back into the potato shells and top with cheese.
Put back into the oven and bake for about 10 minutes. Very elegant and is great with a steak.

title: lime pickles
directions: Mix and pour over cucumbers.
Let set for 24 hours.
Use a crock or glass container.
Wash well.
Let set in cold water for 3 hours.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Make as you would biscuits. Dough will keep in refrigerator several days.

title: pull apart bacon cheese wreath
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cover bottom and sides of a 9-inch round cake pan with foil.
Place 3-inch custard cup in center. Melt Crisco and cheese in small pan on low heat.
Remove and stir until smooth and creamy.
Spread on bottom of pan around cup.
Cut each biscuit into quarters and cover cheese to form a wreath. Bake 14 minutes.
Turn to serving platter.
Remove foil and cut. Sprinkle with crumbled bacon and parsley.
Serve warm.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix cake mix, eggs and margarine well. Spread in bottom of 9 x 13 pan.

title: preserved children
directions: Mix children and dogs well together.
Pour them into God's open field.
Sprinkle with wild flowers.
Spread brook gently over pebbles.
Cover all with the Heavens above in colors of deep blue and the warm sun to bake.
When children are well browned, remove and place in a tub of warm water.
Towel dry.
Put in warm jammies. Say goodnight prayers with a hug and kiss and love you forever.

title: easy cheesie biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Grease heavy biscuit pan and have hot. Sift flour in bowl; add salt and baking powder, sifted.
Mix in shortening with fork.
Add grated cheese; mix together and stir in milk.
Do not overmix.
Drop large spoons of dough on hot, greased pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake in 2 loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quick eclair cake
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar, cocoa and milk.
Bring to a boil and cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and salt. Let cool.

title: little cheesecakes
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs; beat again.
Put cupcake papers into cupcake pan.
Place one vanilla wafer in bottom of each paper.
Top with large tablespoon of filling.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Top each cheesecake with the pie filling of your choice.
Chill completely.

title: mexican salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours to blend flavors; then mix with cheese and shredded lettuce when ready to serve over chips.

title: tomato, spinach and cheese burritos
directions: Process cheeses, chili powder, red pepper and cumin in food processor, or beat in large mixing bowl until smooth.
Coarsely shred half the spinach leaves.
Layer shredded spinach, cheese mixture and tomato in center of each tortilla.
Fold opposite sides of tortilla over filling and place on a baking pan that's been lightly coated with the olive oil cooking spray.
Bake at 400° until golden brown (about 15 minutes).
Divide remaining spinach among 4 plates and arrange burritos atop the leaves.
Serve with salsa and sour cream.
Makes 4 servings.

title: light red velvet cake
directions: Beat butter and cream cheese at medium speed with an electric mixer until creamy; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Gradually add egg substitute, beating well.
Stir in food coloring.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients.
Add to butter mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into three 9-inch round cake pans coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes.
Cool in pans on wire racks 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool completely on wire racks. Contains 278 calories, 42 g protein, 6.1 g fat, 52.1 g carbohydrates and 17 mg cholesterol.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix together pumpkin, milk and soda, add remaining ingredients.
Mix all ingredients and drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: chicken in wine sauce
directions: Sprinkle chicken lightly with thyme and paprika.
Brown quickly, a few at a time, in butter.
While chicken is browning, grease baking dish.
Arrange dried beef and mushrooms on bottom of dish.
Lay chicken on top.

title: apple fritters
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar and salt.
Combine and stir egg, milk and butter into dry ingredients just until smooth; don't overbeat.
Slice apples into rings and dip into batter one at a time.
Heat 1 inch of oil to 375°.
Fry fritters 3 minutes or until brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot, sprinkled with powdered sugar or maple syrup.

title: bean dip
directions: Put all of the ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch glass pan in this order:
Spread the bean dip on the bottom of the pan.
Mix the taco seasoning with the sour cream and put on top of the bean dip. Then spread the guacamole dip on top of that.
Next sprinkle the diced green onions.
Cover the onions with shredded cheese. Sprinkle the sliced onions on top of the cheese.
Finally add the diced tomatoes to the top and the sliced black olives.
Serve chilled with tortilla chips.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour in a 325° oven.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt oleo in deep baking dish.
Use 3/4 cup sugar (less if desired) over peaches and set aside.

title: mom's best chicken
directions: Season chicken pieces with seasoning salt and place in casserole.
Add
chopped vegetables, cover and bake at 250°F for 1 1/2 - 2 hrs.
May also be cooked in electric skillet or stovetop for 1 hr.
Chicken will be juicy.
For gravy:
Remove chicken and blend the rest in blender and add 1/2 c., or more, cream and 1/2 - 1 Tbsp. cornstarch.
Heat thoroughly.

title: steak casserole
directions: Salt and pepper the steak and coat well the cube steaks. Brown in oil on both sides. In well-greased oblong dish (13 x 9), place the steak in the bottom, then layer of potatoes, then the onions. Mix gravy according to directions. Bring to a boil and pour over mixture. Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: key lime pie
directions: Whisk together Key lime juice and condensed milk.
Fold into whipped topping and pour into graham cracker pie crust. Refrigerate for 4 hours and serve.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Mix and shake well and brush on chicken.

title: molded ambrosia salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water; add pineapple.
Cool.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 6-cup mold; chill until firm. Serves 10.

title: dill oyster crackers
directions: Heat oil; do
not
boil.
Mix
with dry Ranch dressing. Stir until blended.
Put
crackers
in
large
bowl.
Sprinkle dill weed on crackers
and
pour oil mixture over them.	After mixing well, until all
oil is absorbed, pour out on newspaper topped with paper towels and let crackers drain well.

title: pound cake
directions: Add enough milk to make real creamy.
Mix will be thick. Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour pound cake pan.
Bake 1 hour or until toothpick stuck in middle comes out clean.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Fold in sour cream.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook mixed vegetables about 20 minutes and drain.
Mix all ingredients, except crackers.
Put in a baking dish.
Put the crackers on top.
Bake at 350° until crackers brown a little.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Wash strawberries; hull.
Simmer 1 cup of strawberries, sugar and water for 15 minutes.
Mix remaining cup with cornstarch; add to cooked strawberries.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly. Cool.
Add uncooked strawberries and cool.
Pour prepared pudding into baked pie shell; top with strawberry mixture.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Whip cream can be substituted for vanilla pudding.
Mix 1/2 pint of heavy cream and 1 teaspoon vanilla together.

title: candied squash
directions: Boil whole squash in a deep kettle 15 minutes.
Drain, split and remove seeds.
Peel; cut into chunks.
Melt butter in a heavy pan.
Stir in sugar, syrup, nutmeg and water.
Add squash and toss well; cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Then uncover for 5 minutes or until tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter in casserole.
After mixing all ingredients fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into casserole and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal and margarine.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Mix in sugars and eggs.
Mix in flour, soda, salt, cocoa and 1/2 of the chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread in greased and floured 9
x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle rest of chocolate chips and nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: sugar-free thousand island dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients with a fork or wire whisk.
Cover and store in refrigerator.
Best when used within 2 weeks.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: corn bread supreme
directions: Variation:
Use 2 eggs and 1 1/2 cups corn meal mix.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Roll out pastry for bottom crust and fit into 9-inch pie pan. Break Ritz crackers coarsely into crust.
Combine water, sugar and cream of tartar in a saucepan and boil gently for 15 minutes.
Add lemon juice and rind.
Cool.
Pour syrup over crackers.
Dot generously with butter or margarine and sprinkle with cinnamon. Cover with top crust, trimming and fluting edging together.
Cut slits in top crust.
Bake in a 425° oven for 30 to 35 minutes until crust is crisp and golden.

title: creamed spinach with mushrooms
directions: Cook spinach; drain and chop.
Melt butter and saute mushrooms.
Blend in flour, nutmeg, salt and pepper, then slowly stir in milk.
Stir until thickened.
Add spinach and heat well. Makes 6 servings.

title: ground turkey casserole
directions: Put 1 pound of turkey in mixing bowl.
Add 1 small chopped onion and Grape-Nuts in 1/2 cup tomato soup.
Add egg, salt and pepper.
Place in loaf pan and top with catsup.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: homemade cajun seasoning
directions: In a small bowl mix all the ingredients well.
Store in an airtight container in a dry place.
Makes 2 tablespoons Cajun Seasoning.

title: elvis presley cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed on box. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: lime salad mold or the green stuff
directions: Melt in top of double boiler the marshmallows and milk.
Pour hot mixture over gelatin and
stir until dissolved.

Cut cream cheese into small chunks and beat into mixture with electric mixer until well blended, then beat in whipping cream and mayonnaise. Pour into mold that has been greased with mayonnaise and chill until firm.

title: burrito casserole
directions: In skillet, cook hamburger and onion. Drain. Add taco seasoning. Add tomato sauce and simmer to blend flavors. In a 9x13 baking dish, begin by layering tortillas. Then add half of the hamburger mixture, half of the can of refried beans, and half of the cheese. Add another layer of tortillas and then repeat with same order. Top with a layer of tortillas and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes. Garnish with lettuce, sour cream, and olives if desired.

title: potato balls(komper)
directions: Boil lightly salted water in a large heavy kettle.
Grate (or grind) the potatoes and strain.
(Discard liquid.)
Empty the grated potatoes from strainer into a big bowl.
Add oatmeal, salt and enough flour to form balls in palm of your hand.
Use a large spoon dipped in cold water.
Put cut up bacon in middle of each ball; roll around so bacon is covered.
Place balls in boiling, salted water.
Let the water boil all the time.
Boil about 1 hour. Shake and use a wooden spoon to move balls around so they don't stick, carefully.
Serve with butter.
May be served with or without broth.
They can also be used when cold.
Slice and fry both sides in butter.
Makes about 12 dumplings.

title: hearty soup mix
directions: Combine.
Store in cool, dry place.
Use within 6 months. Shake before using.
Yields 12 1/2 cups.

title: sweet potato souffl
directions: Boil potatoes and drain. Add remaining ingredients and beat 3 to 5 minutes with electric mixer. Pour into buttered baking dish.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut shortening and flour together.
Mix in egg.
Add cold water, salt and vinegar.
Knead into a ball.
On floured surface roll into pie shells.

title: waffle cookies
directions: Melt margarine, add in eggs, cocoa, sugar, vanilla and flour. Mix together with a mixer.
Stir in nuts.
Heat waffle iron on medium setting, drop batter by teaspoon on each section.
Frost with chocolate frosting.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil and bone chicken and remove meat from bone; break into bite size pieces and set aside.
Saute celery, onion and bell pepper in oleo until tender.
Add soup, sauces, broth and seasonings and simmer one hour.
Add chicken pieces and cooked spaghetti.

title: extra good cookies
directions: Mix flour and soda.
Combine sugar, butter and pudding mix. Beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour. Stir in oats, raisins and nuts.
If dry, add the third egg.
Drop teaspoon on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: steak in sour cream
directions: Cut meat in serving pieces.
Salt,
pepper and flour meat. Brown in butter.
Remove meat; saute onion and mushrooms in butter.
Add sour cream and stir well.
Place meat pieces in casserole.
Pour sour cream mixture over meat.
Cover and cook at 350° for about 1 hour. This is a good recipe for deer steaks.
It cuts the wild taste.

title: glazed chicken wings
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chicken wings, in a saucepan and bring to a boil over moderate heat, whisking occasionally. Reduce heat, simmer mixture, stir occasionally, until slightly thickened.

title: stuffed super burgers
directions: Cream together cream cheese, sour cream and dill weed.
Stir in toasted bread crumbs, mushrooms and olives.
Shape beef into 12 thin patties, 4 to 5-inches in diameter.
Place on equal amount of cheese stuffing in center of each of 6 patties; top with remaining patties, pressing edges together to seat.
Place burgers on grill, 3 to 4-inches, from heat and broil at moderate temperature, 8 to 12 minutes on each side or until done.
Makes 6 servings.

title: jello banana pineapple salad
directions: Mix gelatin according to package directions.
Add pineapple, strawberries and bananas.
Pour half of mixture into a mold; place in refrigerator to set.
Keep remaining gelatin mixture at room temperature.
When refrigerated mixture is completely set, spread sour cream evenly over the top.
Pour remaining gelatin mixture over sour cream, carefully.
Place in refrigerator to set.
Remove from mold.
Garnish before serving.

title: japanese pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles until barely tender to bite (approximately 9 minutes).
Drain, rinse with cold water and drain again.
Cut noodles in short strands.
Mix with dressing and chill it overnight.
The next day, mix cucumber with salt and let stand for approximately 20 minutes.
Rinse well; drain.
Mix with noodles, mushrooms, tomatoes, shrimp and onion.

title: breakfast eggnog
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender.
Blend at high speed until mixture is frothy and instant coffee is dissolved.
Makes 2 servings.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: fish chowder
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add potatoes, carrots and celery. Add 2 cups water and simmer until vegetables are soft.
Add fish (broken in pieces).
Simmer.
Dilute 1 can cream of mushroom soup with 1 can milk and add to first and simmer a few minutes.
Season to taste.
If desired, add a small container frozen corn when adding fish.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Mix together 1 cup peaches, sugar, water and cornstarch.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Place 3 cups peaches in a baked pie crust.
Pour cooked mixture over the fresh peaches.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, onions, and mustard. Roll cream cheese mixture in beef.

title: smothered pork chops
directions: Season meat with salt and pepper.
Lightly flour meat.
Fry meat in oil until golden brown on both sides.
Remove from pan. Add onions and garlic to pan and brown.
Stir in 1 teaspoon of flour and brown.
Put pork chops back in pan.
Add water to cover.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer uncovered for 30 to 40 minutes or until meat is tender.

title: rachel's hominy casserole
directions: Heat soup and cheese over low heat until cheese melts.
Drain hominy and add to soup and cheese mixture with Ro-Tel.
Put in casserole dish and crush corn chips over the top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine celery soup and water.
Mix beef and pork with 1/2 cup of soup mixture and flour.
Make small meatballs and brown.
Add remaining soup mixture and simmer.

title: blueberry sauce
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in small heavy saucepan. Stir in water, add blueberries, bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Boil 1 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve over pancakes, waffles, cheesecake, pound cake or ice cream. 2 cups.

title: baked hash brown potatoes
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Mix all ingredients, except cornflakes.
Place in a greased dish; crush cornflakes, pour on top of potatoes.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
May add green peppers and/or mushrooms.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles until tender. Brown hamburger. Mix Ragu and tomato sauce in large bowl. Pour some mixture in 9 x 12 baking dish. Add noodles, cheese, beef and sauce. Repeat.
Add sliced cheese last on top. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening. Dissolve yeast in 2 tablespoons warm water, then add yeast and milk. Let rise for 1/2 hour. Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together Crisco, margarine, sugar and brown sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake 10 minutes at 375° on ungreased cookie sheet.
Remove from pan and cool on paper bag.

title: snow potatoes
directions: Mix with beater until it looks like mashed potatoes.
Put in oven at 350° and bake for 1/2 hour.
Remove from oven.
Top with mini marshmallows and some nuts.
Put back in oven for 5 minutes or until marshmallows are brown.

title: hearty tortellini soup
directions: In a large saucepan, saute crushed garlic in margarine.
Add chicken broth and tortellini and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add spinach, tomatoes and 1 or 2 breasts of chicken, shredded (optional).
Add oregano and pepper. Serve with fresh Parmesan cheese, crusty bread and a fruit salad.
Easy and delicious. Great for Super Bowl Sunday!

title: granny's pound cake
directions: Soften butter to room temperature.
Cream butter, add sugar, 1/2 cup at a time, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add flour, 1/2 cup at a time, beating well. Mix in vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Turn down heat and bake at 300° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: lo-cal stir-fry italian chicken
directions: Cut
chicken
breasts into chunks or slices.
Mix salt, pepper,
oregano
and flour.
Dredge chicken in flour mixture. Put olive oil and butter/margarine in heated pan.
Add chicken and stir-fry
approximately
to 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes, garlic and coriander to
chicken
and
stir-fry
about
3 to 5 minutes. Add lime juice.
Cover
with
lid and steam briefly. Serve with nutmeg over spinach.

title: real cheese cake
directions: Mix and press in large spring-form pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Mix soup with 1/2 can broth or water and pour over chicken. Add Veg-All (drained) or peas.
Make batter of flour, melted margarine and buttermilk.
Pour evenly over mixture.
Pour 2 cups broth over all. Do not stir.
Bake until brown, about 1 hour at 350°.

title: tropical (and delicious) cheese ball
directions: Thoroughly mix with hands, not mixer.
Form into ball.
Roll in chopped nuts or coconut.
Serve with fancy crackers.
(Easier to form, if chilled first.)

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut tops from the peppers.
Scoop out the seeds and core.
Boil the peppers 10 minutes.
Drain.
Fill with stuffing made of the meat, egg, bread crumbs, milk, salt, pepper and onion.
Place in a deep baking dish.
Pour soup and water over peppers.
Bake about 30 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook syrup, sugar and water until it will spin a thread.
Add peanuts and cook over medium heat until peanuts are well roasted (do not undercook).
Add salt and soda.
Pour on well-greased surface.
Break in serving pieces.

title: taco dip
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients together.
Pour into ovenproof serving dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Heat at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until cheese is bubbly.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk with Cool Whip until smooth.
Pour in lemonade and mix until fluffy.
Pour into pie shell and refrigerate until firm.

title: caramel layer chocolate squares
directions: In a saucepan, melt caramels and 1/2 cup evaporated milk. Set aside. Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: mammaw's divinity
directions: Mix sugar, water and Karo thoroughly.
Boil until mixture forms hard ball.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Slowly pour hot syrup over egg whites.
Add vanilla.
Beat with a wooden spoon until very cool and thick.
Add nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto buttered waxed paper.

title: mother's microwave peanut brittle candy
directions: Cook Karo, sugar, salt and peanuts for 4 minutes on High power.
Stir, then cook, 4 more minutes on High power.
Add butter.
Cook 2 minutes on High power.
Add vanilla and soda. Pour on well buttered foil.
Allow to cool, then break into pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: fantastic chicken
directions: Mix together well.
Arrange chicken (up to 5 pounds) in baking pan.
Cover the chicken with half of the apricot mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Turn chicken.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Combine the soup and Ro-Tel in saucepan. Warm.
Layer tortilla chips, chicken, tortilla chips and chicken.
Pour your cream of mushroom soup and Ro-Tel mixture over your layered chicken and chips.
Pour your cheese over the top and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Set aside. Cut chicken into cubes.
Put in bowl.
Add cornstarch, soy sauce and vinegar.
Cover and refrigerate.
Combine next 5 ingredients. Drain chicken.
Coat in batter.
Stir-fry in small amount of oil.

title: old timers' crackling bread
directions: Add all ingredients and bake until golden brown.
Serve with butter.

title: tuna-yogurt salad
directions: Mash egg yolks in bowl.
Combine with yogurt, mustard and spices.
Add chopped whites and remaining ingredients; mix well. Chill for 1 hour.
Serve with crackers, bagels or toast.
Yields 6 servings.
Contains 114 calories, 2.7 grams fat, 10 grams carbohydrates and 12.3 grams protein per serving.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Saute finely chopped onion with celery and sausage in butter. Add stuffing and poultry seasoning.
Add water to make mixture soft.
Slit pork chops and stuff.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: barbecue
directions: Heat butter and fat.
Brown celery and onions.
Add brown sugar, salt, Worcestershire sauce, red pepper, ketchup, vinegar and dry mustard.
Add chopped sliced meat and simmer several hours.
You can double sauce, depending on amount of meat.

title: yogurt blender pancakes
directions: In blender, blend egg, yogurt and oil until smooth.
Add dry ingredients and blend until smooth.
On a lightly greased, hot griddle, pour 1/4 cup batter for each pancake.
When pancake is covered with bubbles, turn over.
Brown second side.
Serve with butter and syrup.

title: creamy guacamole
directions: Mash avocados and cream cheese with a fork or potato masher. Stir in remaining ingredients, saving the tomato to use as garnish. Serve with your favorite chips.

title: potato balls
directions: Mix grated potatoes and onions, salt, oat bran or oatmeal and flour.
Roll into little balls and fry.
Then pour mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup over them and put in microwave for a few minutes until warm.

title: fresh snack drink
directions: Blend all ingredients 1 minute and chill.
Makes 1 quart.

title: shoney's cabbage soup
directions: Mix well and cook until cabbage is tender.
May have to add water if too thick.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, soup, garlic salt, onion and catsup. Mix in a blender.
Pour into a container and add the beef, which has been cut into small pieces.
Chill for at least 4 hours or overnight.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter; add (heating through but not browning) beef, salt and pepper. Spread in a 2-quart baking dish 3 cups cabbage; cover with meat mixture. Top with other 3 cups cabbage. Pour on top 1 can condensed tomato soup. Bake, covered, for 1 hour. Serves 6.

title: spice tea mix
directions: Mix together.
Use 2 heaping teaspoons of mix in 1 cup hot water for a delicious cup of hot tea.

title: rolled oat clusters
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and salt; stir.
Bring to full boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and peanut butter; stir until smooth.
Add rolled oats; mix well.
Cool slightly; drop by tablespoons onto waxed paper.

title: overnight salad
directions: Layer half of lettuce in a large bowl, then sliced boiled eggs, frozen peas (slightly thawed), salt, pepper, sugar, crumbled bacon, half onion (chopped), bacon, shredded cheese and top with mayonnaise.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: chocolate sour cream frosting
directions: In saucepan, melt chocolate pieces and butter or margarine over low heat, stirring frequently.
Cool about 10 minutes.

Stir in sour cream, vanilla and salt; gradually add powdered sugar, beating by hand until frosting is smooth and of spreading consistency. Frost tops and sides of 2 (8 or 9-inch) layers of about 24 cup cakes.

title: chili con queso
directions: Melt together in top of double boiler.
Serve with unsalted tortilla chips.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter. Add eggs one at a time to the butter/sugar.
Sift together the flour, soda and salt.
Add to mixture alternately with the sour cream. Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Mix flour, milk, sugar, butter and flour to smooth mixture. Pour mixture into well-buttered casserole dish.
Pour peaches on top of mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine.
Mix pretzels, margarine and 1/2 cup sugar.
Bake for 7 minutes.
Cool mixture, but not too long, or it will get too hard.
Break up with a fork. Beat Cool Whip and cream cheese together with mixer.
Add pretzel mixture, drained pineapple and remaining sugar.
Chill.

title: barbecue sauce(special for chicken)
directions: Mix all liquids together; stir in dry ingredients which have been mixed together.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Baste chicken with sauce several times during barbecue process.

title: steak n shake chili
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven; add beef and salt. Cook over low heat until beef looks like rice and is cooked thoroughly.
Drain beef. Put soup in blender; blend 1 minute.
Add soup to beef.
Cover and let simmer 5 minutes.
Add Chili powder, beans, tomato paste, tomato sauce and cola.
Heat through.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef with onion.
Add soup; mix.
Put in greased casserole dish and alternate meat mixture and potatoes (salt potatoes).
Pour milk on top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours, uncovered, at 350°.

title: smoky cheddar cheese ball
directions: Whip
the
first 5 ingredients in blender until smooth. Add small
amount
of milk if needed to ease blending.
Chill until firm enough to handle.
Form into ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain all liquid from beans, rinse the kidney beans. Mix the first seven ingredients together thoroughly and pour over drained beans. Cover tightly and place in refrigerator for several hours before serving.

title: fennel potato and leek soup
directions: Remove core from fennel and slice.
Reserve some sprigs for garnish.
Peel potatoes and chop coarsely.
In medium soup pot, heat butter and oil over low heat.
Add leeks; saute, stirring occasionally until soft.
Add fennel and potatoes; continue sauteing for 10 more minutes, or until softened.
Add chicken stock; bring to simmer.
Partially cover and cook 30 minutes.

title: sausage stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and pat dry. Remove stems. Finely chop stems. Set aside.

title: pasta salad
directions: You can use any veggies you want.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Saute celery, green pepper, onion and garlic in small amount of margarine. Stir in chicken broth, tomatoes and sliced okra. Add spices; add any you like with shrimp.
Simmer for awhile.
Add shrimp and cook just until pink.
If not thick, add 1 tablespoon cornstarch.
This is especially good in the summer using fresh veggies.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Cool and tear into small pieces. Do not use any of the chicken broth.
Cook noodles; drain and rinse in cold water.
Cook vegetables until tender.
Mix together flour and skim milk.
Boil water and bouillon cubes.
Add flour and milk mixture, then add noodles, chicken and vegetables.
Cook 15 minutes on medium heat.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Saute or bake bacon in baking pan.
Shred cabbage and steam in skillet with bacon drippings until almost done.
Spread cabbage in baking pan.
Mix cornbread as directed on box.
Crumble bacon into cornbread mix.
Pour over cabbage in baking pan.
Cook until cornbread is done.

title: sour cream cucumber salad
directions: Toss cucumber with salt in a medium bowl, cover and chill. Stir sour cream, lemon juice, onion, sugar, and white pepper in a small bowl until well blended.
Reserve 1/4 cup of the mixture for garnish.
Combine cucumber with remaining sour cream mixture. Refrigerate 2 hours or until well chilled.
Arrange cucumber slices on a bed of salad greens.
Top with reserved sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle with minced parsley.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Mix coconut, sugar and sour cream together thoroughly and let sit overnight in the fridge.
Next day, cook yellow cake mix according to package directions in 8 or 9-inch layers.
Completely cool.
Split layers.
Pack coconut mixture between layers and on top.
May garnish with nuts or cherries for holidays.
Let cake stand in fridge 3 days before serving.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Drain the juice from the quart of dill pickles.
The pickles don't have to be uniform size.
Into a large bowl, slice the pickles 1/4 inch thick.
Pour over them 2 cups sugar, 1 tablespoon vinegar and 2 tablespoons pickling spices.
Stir gently with wooden spoon.
Let set for several hours at room temperature until sugar dissolves and makes its own syrup.
Now pack back into jar.
Place onion chunk on top; seal and refrigerate for 4 days before using. Turn the jar now and then so all mixes well.
These are crisp and very good.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix well in a large bowl with hand mixer.
Pour in pie shells. Bake in 300° to 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Put in large mixing bowl.
Mix all ingredients together.
Add broth over mixture and stir until about as thick as cornbread. Add more crackers and loaf bread, if needed.
Bake at 300° until done for about 30 minutes.

title: homemade french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender; beat for 5 minutes.
Let stand in refrigerator for 1 hour before serving.
Makes 1 quart.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix all above.
Serve warm with chips.

title: bean casserole
directions: Slice 1 stick butter over beans and heat.

title: cauliflower au gratin
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Saute garlic and ham for 2 minutes. Add cauliflower and cook until crisp-tender.
Combine flour and cream; stir in skillet and blend well.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook until thickened and bubbly.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Place in preheated oven at 350° until cheese has melted and brown on top, about 15 to 20 minutes.
(Broccoli can be substituted.)

title: broccoli cheese chicken
directions: Cook chicken in skillet over medium heat in hot margarine for 10 minutes or until browned on both sides.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup, milk and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer ten minutes or until chicken is fork-tender, stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice.

title: bow tie italian casserole
directions: Cook bow tie pasta; drain and set aside.
Cook ground beef; drain off fat.
To ground beef, add Italian seasoning, pizza sauce, onion and mushrooms.
In another bowl, add egg and cottage cheese.
In a 12 x 9-inch baking pan, layer 1/2 of the pasta, spoon 1/2 of cottage cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of Parmesan cheese.
Layer pepperoni slices (optional).
Place 1/2 of meat mixture.
Next, add 1/2 of Mozzarella and 1/2 of Monterey Jack cheese.
Repeat pasta, cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, pepperoni and meat mixture.
Top with remainder of Mozzarella and Monterey Jack.

Finish top with 1/2 cup shredded Cheddar cheese. Bake, covered, at 425° for 15 minutes; uncover and bake 8 to 10 minutes until cheese is melted and casserole is heated through. Serve with favorite salad and hot bread.

title: cheesecake
directions: Beat in order given.
Grease a 9-inch spring-form pan with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Shut off oven and let stand for 1 more hour.
Remove from oven and let cool completely before removing from pan.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar, flour, eggs, cream, and water. Cook until thick and boiling, stirring constantly. Add vanilla and butter; stir well.

title: corn dip or dish
directions: Mix all ingredients and top with Fritos before serving as a dish, or use as a dip, serve with dipping size chips.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar until smooth.
Add mayonnaise mixture to other ingredients and refrigerate for several hours.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar, vanilla and oil.
Add zucchini, pineapple and walnuts.
Stir together 3 cups flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Fold into egg mixture to combine.
Divide between two 4 x 9-inch greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for an hour, or until done.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and beat.
Mix in pumpkin.
Add evaporated milk.
Add spices.
Mix well and pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle yellow cake mix over mixture.
Melt margarine and pour evenly over cake mix.
Add pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: moist 'n crispy onion chicken
directions: Place the onion soup mix and the bread crumbs in a large plastic food bag and shake.
Brush the chicken on all sides with mayonnaise.
Place the chicken, one piece at a time, in the bag. Close tightly and shake.
Place chicken on a rack in the broiler pan. Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: rhubarb salad
directions: Put rhubarb, sugar and salt in pan on low heat.
Do not stir or add water.
When tender, quickly bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Dissolve.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill until slightly thickened and spoon into molds.
Serves 8.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar.
Gradually add eggs; mix until well blended.
Sift all dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Add pumpkin, vanilla and raisins.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream the cream cheese and margarine together.
Add flour, pepper and salt.
Blend well.
Squeeze through a cookie press onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Makes 6 dozen straws.
These freeze great.

title: applesauce-raisin cake
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased, long pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: elmer's glue dough
directions: Mix and knead all until blended.
Dough will be sticky at first.
If necessary, add more cornstarch or flour.
Use glue to fasten parts together.
Paint with Elmer's glue paint (add food coloring to white glue and stir), then spray with clear acrylic.

title: amaretti(almond macaroons)
directions: Sift sugars with flour and salt; set aside.
In medium bowl, break up almond paste with wooden spoon.
Add egg whites and beat until well blended and fairly smooth.
Stir in flour mixture until well blended.
Drop by slightly rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart on cookie sheet that is lined with aluminum foil and greased. Lightly shape into rounds.
Press pignoli nuts into each.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until golden.
Let cool slightly, carefully remove to rack.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Melt chocolate pieces.
Add milk, vanilla, salt and nuts. Pour into waxed paper-lined 8-inch square pan.

title: crawfish bisque soup
directions: Saute onions and peppers in butter until soft.
Add roux; stir well.
Add crawfish.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add liquid crawfish boil, cream and milk.
Cook on low heat about 30 to 40 minutes.
Stir often.
Use parsley for garnish.
Serve with slices of garlic bread or French bread.

title: peach delight
directions: Pour peaches in bottom of oblong pan, juice and all.
Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly on top.
Add nuts and the slices of oleo on top.
Do not stir in.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Let cool and put Cool Whip on.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: On a very low flame, melt butter in large pan and add cream (slowly), stirring constantly.
Then add cheese (slowly), stirring constantly, until mixture is thick.
When this occurs, it's ready to pour over the cooked noodles.

title: frosted cake
directions: Add the sugar to the well beaten eggs.
Sift the cake flour and baking powder.
Beat into the egg mixture.
Continue beating and add vanilla.
Scald the milk and add the butter.
Add to the cake mixture.
Pour into a buttered 9 X 9 pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mexican fiesta medley
directions: Saute beef and onion in a large skillet.
Stir in soup, water and tomatoes.
Top with chips and heat 5 to 7 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top and serve hot.
If the skillet is covered during the heating time, the chips will be soft like enchiladas.

title: strawberry crunch
directions: In an 8 x 12-inch dish, smooth the strawberry pie filling, then pineapple on top of that.
Then sprinkle the dry cake mix on top.
Pour melted butter or margarine on top of dry cake mix, then put chopped nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Flour pork chops and brown in oil.
Put in a baking dish.
Put mushrooms over pork chops.
Cook chopped onion in half stick of butter.
Add milk, flour and curry powder.
Bring all of the ingredients to a boil, stirring all the time.
Pour over pork chops and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for at least 1 hour.

title: lemon pie
directions: Separate the eggs.
Mix the yolks with milk and lemon juice. Pour into crust.
Make a meringue of the egg whites by beating the whites until stiff.
Gradually mix in 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pile on the pie and bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook and drain noodles. Melt margarine and pour over macaroni. Mix soup and evaporated milk. Beat eggs into milk. Combine macaroni and grated cheese. Salt and pepper to taste. Mix together all ingredients in a large bowl and pour into crock-pot. Top with reserved cheese and paprika. Cook 3 hours on low.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple with juice and pie filling. Stir in Cool Whip, marshmallows, nuts, cherries and bananas. Chill and serve.

title: plain pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add eggs, one at a time (unbeaten), beating after each addition.
Add the flour gradually. Add baking powder with last addition of flour.
Add water and vanilla.
Bake in a small angel food pan for 1 hour at 300°.

title: veg-all chicken pot pie
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients; spoon into pie shell.
Cover with top crust.
Seal.
Slit the top and brush with egg.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Very easy.

title: tomato rice soup with ham
directions: Cook bacon in large saucepan on medium heat until lightly browned.
Add onion and ham; cook and stir until onion is tender. Stir in tomatoes, corn, water, tomato sauce, bouillon cube, thyme and pepper; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in rice; cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Garnish with parsley if desired.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix cake mix per instructions on box.
Bake in thin layers. It runs from 7 to 9 layers.

title: tacos
directions: Put meat in a pan.
Put it in the oven.
Then you eat them. You put cheese and salad on, then hot sauce.

title: sausage skillet supper
directions: Brown sausage, onion and bell pepper in large skillet until meat is brown and onions are translucent.
Drain fat off and return to skillet.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil. Cover and simmer about 30 minutes.
Especially good over mashed potatoes.

title: mint sauce
directions: Stir ingredients until blended.
Serve with lamb.

title: lazarus baked chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crumbs and cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Mix cheese and crumbs.
Place on top and bake 20 minutes longer.

title: spanish pork chops
directions: In a large skillet, brown 4 pork chops and set aside.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in pan and add rice-vermicelli mixture.
Cook until vermicelli is light brown.
Add 2 1/2 cups hot water, contents of envelopes and 1 can stewed tomatoes.
Stir.
Return chops to skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.

title: easy sherbet punch
directions: In a large bowl or pitcher,
spoon sherbet by the tablespoon. Add orange juice and lemon juice, stirring to mix sherbets. Slowly pour chilled lemon-lime carbonated beverage over sherbet. Stir gently to mix.
Makes 36 (4 ounce) servings.

title: beaufort stew
directions: Cover corn, potatoes and sausage with water.
Add salt and black pepper.
Bring to a boil.
When potatoes are almost done, add other ingredients.
Boil 8 to 10 minutes.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Drain and serve.

title: chocoroons
directions: Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: barbecue hamburger
directions: Brown meat, celery and onion in skillet.
Add other ingredients and salt to taste.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.
Very good and easy to double.

title: biscuit mix
directions: Cut together and store in a covered container in the refrigerator. One cup mix makes 3 or 4 biscuits when combined with 1/2 to 3/4 cup whole milk. Shape into biscuit shapes and bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: apple peanut salad
directions: In large bowl, combine apples, peanuts and whipped topping. Cover and refrigerate until serving.
Yields 10 servings.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain.
Mix cottage cheese, eggs, parsley, butter, salt, pepper and garlic powder in bowl.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place layer of noodles in pan followed by layers of cottage cheese mixture, Monterey Jack cheese, spinach and Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: mexican curry
directions: Saute onions and peppers.
Add curry powder and flour. Gradually stir in milk and tomato sauce.
Heat until bubbly.
Add meat and simmer 45 minutes.
Spoon over noodles or rice.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Melt butter on medium heat, don't burn.
Then add crushed graham crackers and mix well.
Put into an oblong pan and pat into bottom with hands.
Bake 10 minutes in 350° oven.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Dissolve unflavored gelatin in 1/4 cup water and let sit. Heat tomato soup and add cream cheese.
Stir until mixed and add gelatin.
Add mayo, celery and onion.
Add shrimp and salt.
Put in a mold.
Chill in fridge until firm.
Serve with sesame crackers.

title: zucchini hot cakes
directions: Melt one tablespoon of butter in skillet and spoon two tablespoons of batter on. Flatten and brown on both sides. Serve with syrup like pancakes.

title: hearts of gold
directions: Pour butter over grated cheese; mix well. Add flour and cayenne pepper gradually. Pinch off dough the size of a marble. Flatten and put a nut into the center. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 20 minutes.
These can be frozen or refrigerated.
Remove about 1 hour before serving.

title: mexican salad bowl
directions: Tip:
The Cheddar cheese will be easier to shred if you put it in the freezer for 30 minutes before shredding.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in a Dutch oven and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Strain and discard spices. Great for holidays.

title: orange blossoms
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and chill.
Make into small balls; roll in coconut or nuts (nice to do part in each).
Stores well and makes lots.
Sort of tart, not too sweet.
Refrigerate or freeze until ready to use.

title: apricot salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Drain pineapple, saving juice.
Stir pineapple into Jell-O.
Refrigerate until partly set.

title: spinach and cheese squares(spankopetes)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, mix Ricotta and eggs. Stir in crumbled Feta.
Add chopped onion and spinach. Layer cookie sheet with phyllo dough.
Butter eat sheet till half of the package is used.
Pour the cheese mixture over the dough layers and spread evenly.
For added flavor, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese over this.
Layer again with phyllo buttering each layer to finish the remainder of the package.
Refrigerate 1 hour. Then cut into 2 inch squares and bake till golden brown.
Use pan the size of phyllo dough to eliminate trimming.
Good reheated in oven at low temperature.

title: mud puddle cake
directions: Place dry ingredients directly into 9-inch square or round pan.
Mix well.
Make a hole or well in the middle of dry ingredients by pushing ingredients to the side of pan.
Pour all liquid ingredients into hole.
Slowly mix ingredients using fork to work in all together.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: ice cream cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add yolk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour; mix and drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Beat together first seven ingredients.
Add crab.
Place in fireproof dish and cover with sliced almonds. Bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: old-fashion cracklin cornbread
directions: In a large bowl, mix flour and corn meal.
Add cooled butter with back of spoon in rubbing fashion until butter is well mixed. Then add milk and eggs once batter is mixed. Drain all liquid off of cracklins. Pat them dry, then add to batter.
Mix well and bake in greased 10-inch skillet until top is golden brown.

title: peanut butter candy cups
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients until smooth.
Press into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread melted chocolate on top.
Refrigerate until slightly firm.
Warm slightly at room temperature and cut into squares.

title: penny puffs
directions: Mix all together.
Make into small round balls.
Can punch down with fork.
Bake at 425° until they begin to brown.
Watch carefully.
If desired, a touch of paprika or Tabasco can be added.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Cook onion in margarine.
Combine all ingredients, except corn flakes, in 9 x 13-inch baking dish, mixing in hash browns last. Bake 45 minutes at 350° until golden brown.
Top with crushed cornflakes for the last 10 minutes of baking.

title: sauce for meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan; stir over medium heat until hot.
Pour over meatballs.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken breast.
Save broth.
Place cut up chicken in 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour 2 cups broth over chicken.
Add cream of chicken soup.
Mix milk, butter and flour. Pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: super spud casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bacon bits, and place in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with bacon bits.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs. Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix butter and sugar until creamy.
Add flour, then gradually add remaining ingredients.
Beat well.
Divide mixture into 2 (9-inch) pie crusts.
Bake at 400° for the first 15 minutes or until the center of the pie is firm.

title: biscuit mix
directions: Place flour in a large bowl; stir in baking powder, salt, cream of tartar and sugar.
Cut in shortening until evenly distributed.
Store in airtight plastic covered container.
It will keep up to 6 months at room temperature.

title: graham cracker squares
directions: Melt butter. Add sugar and boil for 2 minutes, until thick. Line cookie sheet with foil; spread out crackers. Pour melted butter mixture over crackers. Sprinkle nuts over this. Bake 5 to 7 minutes at 350°.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars together.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in salt, soda and flour.
Add about 2 cups M&M's. Drop by teaspoons and bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: holiday breakfast casserole
directions: Beat thoroughly milk, eggs and mustard.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan layer bread cubes, cheese and sausage.
Pour egg mixture over all and refrigerate overnight.
In the morning, pour 1 can soup mixed with 1/2 cup evaporated milk.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until set.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Crumble crackers and mix with asparagus spears and grated cheese in small baking dish. Make medium white sauce: Melt 3 Tbsp. butter add 3 tablespoons flour and mix until smooth. Add 1 1/2 cups liquid. Stir until a medium thickness. Pour white sauce over mixture in baking dish. Mix well. Cover top with cracker crumbs, grated cheese and butter. Bake at 375° in a preheated oven until golden brown.

title: cauliflower broccoli salad
directions: Just before serving, add bacon and sunflower seeds.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed.
Pour half in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 6 minutes. Melt caramels in milk.
Sprinkle top of cake with nuts and chocolate chips.
Drizzle caramel over cake.
Pour rest of cake batter on top.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cake is better baked ahead of time to be served.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: In a large bowl with electric mixer, combine cream cheese and sugar until well blended.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Place slices of banana evenly over crust.
Sprinkle with some lemon juice (to keep bananas from turning black).
Spoon cream mixture over bananas. Combine pie filling and fresh berries; spread over mixture. Refrigerate for at least 4 hours before serving.

title: country tea
directions: Bring 1 pint
water to boil in pan.
Add tea bags and turn stove off and let steep, covered, for 8 to 10 minutes.
Put sugar in pitcher.
Pour tea and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add 9 cups water.
Stir.
Pour over ice; add lemon and enjoy.

title: 1 minute chocolate icing
directions: Mix and boil 1 minute.
Remove and beat by hand until right consistency.
When spreading, work fast.

title: matterhorn chicken
directions: Split, bone and skin chicken breasts.
Flatten chicken breasts to 1/4 inch thick.
Sprinkle each piece with salt.
Top with 1/2 teaspoon of onion and 1/4 cup of cheese.
Fold chicken over cheese.
Secure with toothpicks.
Dip chicken in eggs; coat with bread crumbs.
Brown in oil.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serve over noodles.
Serves 8.

title: minty hot chocolate
directions: Crush butter mints. Mix ingredients together in large Ziploc bag or other seal container. Add 4 heaping tablespoonfuls to a cup of hot water or milk. Makes enough mix for 68 cups of hot chocolate.

title: crabmeat quiche
directions: Bake pie shell at 400° for 5 minutes; cool.
Combine mayonnaise, flour, eggs and milk.
Mix until blended.
Saute onions in butter. Add crabmeat, cheese and sauteed onions to above mixture.
Pour into pastry lined plate.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Prepare noodles and mix all ingredients well.
Put in greased casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered.

title: broccoli stuffed tomatoes
directions: Wash tomatoes; cut off tops and scoop out pulp, leaving shells intact.
Sprinkle cavities of tomatoes with salt and pepper. Invert on wire rack to drain 30 minutes.

title: italian macaroni
directions: Place beef roast in large, heavy kettle with margarine or butter; brown all sides.
Remove meat; add onions and thinly sliced garlic.
Cook slowly for 15 minutes.
Add the tomatoes, tomato paste and bay leaves.
Return meat to kettle; cook very slowly, until sauce has a thick, oily texture, the longer the better.
Salt to taste.

title: dream salad
directions: Make jello according to directions.
Chill until slightly set. Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add jello and beat well.
Fold in fruit; pour into mold and top with nuts.
Chill until set. Serves 8 to 10.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Set aside egg slices.
Mix all other ingredients well.
Stir in egg slices.
Top with buttered bread crumbs and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pizza dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serve warm with tortilla chips, crackers or anything!

title: shrimp creole
directions: You may add any other kind of seafood or substitute chicken for shrimp.

title: cream puff pastry
directions: Add butter to boiling water.
Stir until butter melts.
Add flour and salt all at once. Beat until blended.
Heat, stirring vigorously until mixture is smooth and forms soft ball that doesn't separate.
Cool mixture slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat vigorously after each egg is added.
Beat until smooth.
Drop 1/4 cup batter onto greased cookie sheet for cream puffs.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or 25 minutes at 325°.
Fill with cooked custard or whipped cream.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and sour cream; add garlic powder to taste. Layer ingredients as listed in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: peanut patties
directions: Mix in large saucepan: sugar, water and syrup and bring to a boil.
Add peanuts and food color.
Cook over medium flame until hard ball stage (250°).

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Mix together sugar, vinegar and oil.
Salt and pepper to own taste.
Pour this over
vegetables and let sit overnight.
Longer it sits, better it is.

title: country-style pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together all ingredients except for the cheese.
Pour into pan. Bake for 15 miinutes.
Then sprinkle top with the cheese and bake 20 minutes longer.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Add water to pineapple liquid to measure 1/2 cup.
Soak unflavored gelatin in this.
Dissolve cranberry sauce over low heat.
When dissolved, add 2 cups water.
Heat well.
Dissolve cherry and unflavored gelatin mixture in hot cranberry mixture. Add pineapple, celery, nuts, etc.
Put in dish and refrigerate.

title: pumpkin sheet cake
directions: Mix together and pour into 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: bridge dessert
directions: Mix together and pat into pan.

title: jellied cottage cheese fruit salad
directions: Line two 8 x 8-inch pans with freezer wrap or foil.
Allow enough extra wrap to fold over top.
Dissolve gelatin in water. Stir in fruit liquid.
Stir in cheese and fruits.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into each pan.
Chill until firm.
Makes 12 servings, about 3/4 cup each.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Using a lasagne pan, shred lettuce and line dish.
Layer in order:
celery, onion, green pepper, green beans, salt and pepper. Combine mayonnaise and Blue Cheese.
Spread over top.
Sprinkle crumbled bacon over top.
Refrigerate 8 hours.
Keeps in refrigerator 1 to 2 days nicely.

title: oatmeal waffles
directions: In a large mixing bowl, stir together flour, oats, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
In a small mixing bowl, stir together eggs, milk, margarine and brown sugar.
Add to flour mixture all at once.
Stir just until blended.
Pour 1 to 1 1/2 cups batter onto grids of preheated, lightly greased waffle baker.
Close lid quickly; do not open during baking.
Bake according to manufacturer's directions.
When done, use a fork to remove waffle. Makes 4 waffles.

title: four bean salad
directions: Combine sugar, oil and vinegar.
Pour over remaining ingredients and refrigerate.

title: super beef and squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in salt water about 5 minutes.
Drain well; set aside.
Cook green pepper and ground beef until meat is no longer pink.
Stir in rice.
Blend eggs, soup, sour cream and seasoning and stir into meat mixture.
Fold in squash mixture and turn into a greased, shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 or 9-inch square baking pan. Melt butter over low heat.
Mix together cocoa and sugar, then stir in the melted butter.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir again.
Now add the flour and salt; mix until smooth.
Do not overmix.
If you want to add chopped nuts, now's the time to do so.
Pour mixture into the baking pan and spread evenly.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes or until the brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan or a toothpick comes out clean when inserted in the center of the brownies.

title: mama's beef stew
directions: Flour stew meat.
In a skillet, heat 2 to 3 tablespoons oil; brown stew meat.
Transfer to a boiler.
Add 1 large can chopped tomatoes, chopped onion and 1/2 cup water.
Let simmer slowly. Chop carrots and potatoes.
Add after stew has simmered 45 minutes.
Then simmer 45 minutes more.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, 4 tablespoons sugar and margarine in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 400° for 6 minutes.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Make thick white sauce: melt butter; slowly add flour. Stir often.
Gradually add milk; when smooth add 2 cups grated cheese. Stir until cheese is melted completely.

title: darleen's crab dip
directions: Put all ingredients in ovenproof dish.
Bake at 325° for approximately 20 minutes until bubbly.
Take out of oven.
Mix well.
Serve with assorted crackers.
Serves 12.

title: candy covered nuts
directions: Combine sugar and water on high heat until sugar is melted. Add the raw peanuts.
