Continue cooking until sugar turns back to sugar.
Pour onto cookie sheet and bake in a 250° oven for 1 hour. Stir once in a while to keep nuts separated.

title: cinnamon chocolate cake
directions: Sift together in bowl the flour, sugar, salt and cinnamon. In saucepan, combine cocoa, margarine, shortening and water. Bring to a rapid boil and pour over flour mixture. Mix as soon as removed from heat. Mix well, then add eggs one at a time and beat well. Add buttermilk and baking soda. Bake in greased and floured pan as follows:

title: mustard barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, and mix well.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Add flour a little at a time and mix well.
Roll out and cut into shapes or roll into small balls and pat thin.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° about 7 minutes.

title: zucchini and rice casserole
directions: Butter a 3-quart casserole.
Layer as follows:
rice, chicken, cheese (save 1 cup), zucchini and tomato.
Mix sour cream, chilies, oregano, garlic salt, green pepper and onion in a separate bowl.
Pour over layered casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and parsley.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 325°.

title: cheesy chicken casserole
directions: Gently simmer whole chicken or chicken breasts in salted boiling water just to cover 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until tender. Remove chicken, let cool.
Remove skin, remove chicken from bone. Cook broccoli as package label directs.
Drain and arrange in bottom of greased 8 x 10-inch oblong casserole.

title: steve's peach dumplings
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, butter and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Add enough milk to make stiff like pie dough.
Roll out, put peaches on dough and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Roll, cut and put dumplings in pan and pour dressing over.

title: purple cows
directions: You will need 4 tall glasses.

title: peas and rice
directions: Fry salt pork or bacon in heavy skillet.
Add onions and saute until lightly browned.
Add tomato paste and peas to the water; add the juice from the cans of peas to make the 4 cups.
Bring to boil. Add salt, pepper, thyme and rice; cook on medium heat until all the water is absorbed.
Add the cooking oil and cover tightly.
Cook on low heat until rice is done.

title: spoonbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour in greased 13 x 9 pan. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until lightly brown on top and firm to the touch.

title: macaroon pie
directions: Beat
egg whites until foamy.
Fold in cream of tartar, beat until stiff.
Fold in sugar, crackers, nuts and vanilla. Spread in	buttered
cake	pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Let	cool. Whip
cream stiff, fold in preserves and spread on pie.
Let stand before cutting.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients in a flat baking dish and place in a slow oven at 350° and bake for 1 1/2 hours, or until rice is perfectly tender and pudding is thick and creamy, not dry. Stir every 15 minutes with a fork. Carefully turning under the brown top and and scraping the edges down.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Put hamburger in pan in oven and cook at 350° until done (also onions and peppers if you like).
Drain liquid from meat.
Pour pizza sauce over meat and return to oven to warm.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese (and mushrooms if you like) over sauce.
Put in oven until cheese begins to melt.
Place crescent rolls (unfolded) over mixture.
Cook at 375° until rolls are done (approximately 13 minutes).
Turn over when serving.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix on low speed and then add poppy seeds and water.
Beat 3 minutes.
Pour into lightly greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45-50 minutes.
Drizzle icing over cake if desired.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and whipped topping in a bowl.
Sprinkle jello over top.
Mix well.
Add pineapple and oranges.
Mix gently.
Chill or freeze.

title: coconut party bars
directions: Combine flour, 1/2 cup brown sugar and butter or margarine until particles are fine.
(Use low speed of mixer.)
Press into bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until creamy. Gradually add sugar; beat until peaks are stiff.
Fold in nuts, bits and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on foil covered cookie sheets.
Place in preheated oven and immediately turn off oven. Do not open until morning.

title: pizza cups
directions: * Sausage, hamburger, pepperoni, ham, olives, onions, peppers and pineapple can be used.

title: russian tea
directions: Bring to a boil sugar and 8 cups water.
Add cloves and cinnamon.
In a separate saucepan, bring 2 cups water to a boil. Remove from heat and add tea.
Steep about 5 minutes.
Combine both mixtures.
Just before serving, add orange and lemon juices.

title: lemon-tarragon chicken
directions: Flatten or cut the chicken breasts into strips.
Dredge chicken lightly in flour, tarragon , salt and pepper.
Melt a small amount of oleo in pan.
Saute garlic and add chicken, cook for 5 minutes.
Add pimentos, mushrooms and artichokes; simmer about 5 minutes.
Add enough cornstarch and water thickener to make sauce; add juice of 1 lemon.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix and press into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until brown. Cool.

title: sumi salad
directions: Crush noodles to 1/2-inch pieces and set aside until ready to add dressing.

title: easy turkey divan
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Arrange turkey in greased baking dish (11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch).
Top with hot broccoli.
Cover with cheese. Stir together milk and soup.
Pour over cheese. Bake, uncovered, 25 minutes. Sprinkle with onion rings and bake 5 minutes longer.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: asparagus salad
directions: Heat soup and cream cheese until melted.
Add Jell-O, stirring until dissolved.
Add water, onion, green pepper, celery and salt. Mix.
Pour into mold and chill, then add asparagus.
Return to refrigerator until set.

title: hot chocolate sauce
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, butter, whipping cream, corn syrup and salt.
Cook until mixture comes to a boil.
Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat; stir in Nestle Choco Bake and vanilla extract. Serve warm over cake or ice cream.

title: almond crunch
directions: Melt butter and add sugar, corn syrup and water.
Cook to 300° (watch above 280°).
Stir in nuts.
Spread with cup of melted chocolate; cool.
Break into pieces.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Brown bacon.
Put all ingredients in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.
Stir after they have been baking for an hour.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Mix sugar, sour cream, marshmallows, oleo and salt in pan. Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat to low and boil, without stirring, to soft ball stage, about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, chocolate chips and peanuts.
Stir to blend and melt chips.
Drop from teaspoon onto foil or greased cookie sheet.
If it becomes too firm to drop, heat slightly.

title: louisiana jambalaya
directions: Brown the meats (which you have seasoned to taste) in a little water.
Add chopped onions, bell peppers and celery.
Cook over low heat until soft, stirring often.
Add tomato and beans; cook over medium heat for 45 minutes.
Add hot rice; mix well and cook 10 minutes more, then serve.

title: coconut sour cream cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions, making 2 (9-inch) layers.
Cool and slice each layer to make 4 layers.

title: "tallerine"(whole meal in one)
directions: Brown ground beef and saute onion.
Add to ground meat, Worcestershire, cumin, Tabasco, garlic and tomato sauce.
Cook noodles in salted water according to package directions; drain. Place noodles in casserole.
Stir corn and peas into meat mixture and pour over noodles; mix well.
Sprinkle cheese on top, cover and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
May be frozen.
Wrap well with foil.

title: oven porcupines
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix meat, rice, 1/2 cup water, onion, salts, garlic powder and pepper.
Shape mixture by rounded tablespoons into balls.
Place meatballs in ungreased baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2 inches.
Stir together remaining ingredients; pour over meatballs.
Cover with aluminum foil; bake 45 minutes.
Uncover; bake 15 minutes longer.
Serves 4-6.

title: pineapple chess pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Melt butter.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake about 30 minutes in a 375° oven or a little longer at 350°.
Use unbaked shell.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss everything together and chill.
Change the sweetness to more or less according to your taste.

title: shrimp and crab salad
directions: Mix all ingredients with as little mayonnaise as possible. Refrigerate overnight and serve cold.

title: creamed mushroom chicken with biscuits
directions: Cook chicken in salt water until done.
Let cool.
Pick chicken from bones.
Make a rich gravy with shortening, flour, salt (if needed), pepper, cream of mushroom soup, milk and broth. Cook until boiling, stirring often.
When it boils, stir in chicken pieces; bring to a boil.
Pour chicken mixture in an 11 x 14-inch baking dish.
Place in 350° to 400° oven until a scum forms on the top.
Place biscuits on top and bake until biscuits are done.
Serve with salad and a vegetable.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and boil until they fall apart when stick with a fork.
Drain.
Beat potatoes with a mixer on high speed until smooth.
Add margarine and beat more.
Gradually add enough milk to make potatoes fluff and not stiff.

title: perfect nut cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add egg, then vanilla and flour. Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press one Macadamia nut in center of cookie and bake for 20 minutes at 275°.

title: salmon patties
directions: Open salmon. Heat oil in pan. Dice onion. Add egg and mix. Add crackers. Make patties. Cook on top of stove for several minutes, until done.

title: bran flakes muffins
directions: Mix bran flakes and milk together and let set until bran flakes are soft.
Add egg and butter; mix well.
Sift together remaining dry ingredients.
Add to bran flakes mixture.
Bake in 400° oven for 35 minutes.

title: herbed chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Stew breasts and cool, reserving 2 cups of the broth.
Remove the chicken from the bone and tear into bite-size pieces.
Place in shallow 3-quart baking dish.
Add broccoli.
Combine soups and 1 cup of the broth.
Pour over chicken.
Mix butter and remaining cup of broth.
Stir in stuffing.
Spoon over chicken.
Bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed shrimp
directions: Mix crab with bread crumbs according to how much you want each shrimp stuffed.
Add heavy cream just to help keep stuffing together.
Stuff shrimp and wrap with 1 slice of raw bacon. Secure bacon with toothpick.
Broil or barbecue until done.
Can baste with melted butter.

title: date candy
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, melted oleo and dates.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Scorches easily.
Cook until you can handle.
Add nuts and Rice Krispies.
Mix well.
Dampen your hands and spoon a small amount in your hand.
Form a ball and roll in coconut.

title: yummy cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and oleo in a saucepan. Bring to a rolling boil. Remove from heat. Add peanut butter and vanilla. Quickly add oatmeal and stir while still hot. Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper and cool.

title: frozen lima beans and smoked sausage casserole
directions: Soak beans in water about 30 minutes; drain.
Put beans in 1 1/2-quart casserole, then mix soup with water.
Put over beans. Cut up smoked sausage, put on top.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour. Cover the first 30 minutes.

title: roast turkey
directions: Clean inside and outside of turkey.
Drain bird.
Inside the cavity place bouillon cubes, onion, celery and carrots.
After the bird is cooked these can be discarded.
On the outside of bird sprinkle seasoned salt or lemon and pepper, paprika or melted butter.
Or you can lay on a couple of slices of smoked bacon. Add 2 cups water to pan.
Roast at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes per pound.
Roast at 325° for a larger bird and also a bit longer.

title: sicilian chicken
directions: Heat oil; add onion, green pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 10 minutes.
Cut chicken into 2-inch pieces.
Add to onion mixture. Cook, stirring until pinkness is gone.
Add remaining ingredients, cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Combine margarine, flour and pecans, mixing well.
Press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: mint jelly
directions: To mint leaves, add boiling water and lemon juice.
Let stand 1 hour.
Add sugar.
Bring to boiling point and strain.
Add Certo and green color to make delicate green.
Bring to the boiling point and boil hard for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and pour in jelly glasses.
To double the recipe, use 1 full bottle of Certo.

title: pasta spaghetti salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and let set in refrigerator a few hours before serving.

title: cheesy egg burritos
directions: Melt margarine in skillet over low heat.
Mix eggs and milk. Pour into skillet.
Cook slowly, stirring occasionally, until eggs begin to set.
Add Velveeta and continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until cheese melts and eggs set.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix together, but don't mix to much. Then fry on medium hot griddle till done on both sides.
You can double this recipe.

title: oriental burgers
directions: In a medium bowl, combine beef, onion soup mix and water chestnuts (chopped up fine).
Mix well.
Grill, broil or fry. Place on buns.
Put 1 slice of pineapple and sweet and sour sauce on each.
Enjoy.

title: date pie
directions: Place dates and water in pan to boil.
Cook 5 minutes.
Mix flour and sugar together and place in date mixture until thickened; boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in lemon juice. Place mixture in pie crust and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 425°.

title: mexican baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger, mango, onion and salt and pepper.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hamburger and noodles
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Boil noodles to taste.
Add mushroom soup, chicken soup, sour cream and corn.
Add noodles when done.
Heat and eat.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy bars and one stick of butter in sauce pan.
Set aside.
Cream sugar and butter together.
Add eggs one at a time beating after each one.
Sift flour and mix into sugar mixture. Add buttermilk and mix.
Now add candy mixture and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325 degrees for 1 hour or until done.
Cool.

title: (something good)
directions: Boil chicken in 4 cups of water.
When done, take chicken off bone.
Place back in broth and bring to a boil.
Add soup, stirring until smooth.
Add sour cream.
Salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle in paprika.
Serve over noodles.

title: itsy-ritsy
directions: Mix crackers and melted butter; save some for topping.
Place crushed crackers in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix ice cream (softened), milk and instant pudding.
Place ice cream mixture on top of crackers.
Spread with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with remaining cracker mixture.
Freeze.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix margarine, onions, water and broccoli and cook until dry. Add cheese, soup, milk and rice.
Simmer until cheese is melted. Pour into greased casserole dish and top with 1 cup crushed Ritz crackers, mixed with 1/4 cup melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of celery soup

title: raisin spice drops
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet.
In medium bowl, combine flour, cinnamon, soda, salt and nutmeg.
In large bowl, beat together butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in oats, raisins and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto prepared cookie sheet.
Bake about 8 minutes or until a light brown.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet; remove to wire cooling rack.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: crunchy oven chicken
directions: Combine potato chips, garlic powder, pepper and seasoned salt. Dip chicken into melted butter and roll in potato chip mixture. Place chicken, so it does not touch, in a shallow baking pan. Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 375°.
It's best to turn chicken over after 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all together and serve out of a hot plate with chips or crackers.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake by directions on package.
Take half of cake and crumble in bottom of punch bowl.
Add 1 box pudding (made by directions on box).
Layer these ingredients:
half pie filling, 1/2 pineapple, 1/2 bananas, 1/2 strawberries and 1/2 small Cool Whip.
Repeat, using remaining ingredients.
Top with cherries and nuts.
Serves 20 to 25.
(Use a punch bowl or large bowl.)

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Shape into a loaf.
Put in loaf pan or pie plate (glass).
Cook in microwave on High 5 minutes.
Turn.
Cook another 2 minutes on High.
Top with Mozzarella.
Serve.

title: special hash brown potatoes(microwave)
directions: Slit package and microwave potatoes 10 to 12 minutes, turning once.
Empty potatoes into a shallow 2-quart casserole.
Add milk, salt and chives; mix.
Dot with butter.
Microwave, uncovered, 5 to 6 minutes, or until mixture comes to a boil.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Microwave 4 to 5 minutes more. Serves 6 to 8.

title: gay cauliflower
directions: Break cauliflower into flowerets and cook in small amount of boiling salted water until tender (8 to 12 minutes).
Meanwhile, place the cheese soup, milk, pepper, pimento and Tabasco in saucepan.
Cover and cook slowly until it starts to boil.
Drain cauliflower and pour the sauce over it.
Serve immediately. Yield: 8 servings.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Peel eggplants and cut into slices.
Dip slices into egg and milk mixture.
(Beat eggs and milk together in a bowl.)
Once slices of eggplants are dipped in egg mixture, dip in bread crumbs. Fry in oil until brown and drain well on paper towels.
Place layer of eggplants in casserole, cover with layer of Mozzarella cheese, cover with layer of sauce and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Repeat procedure until all eggplants are used.
Bake in oven about 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix lightly. Add rice. Mix and pour into casserole or flat baking dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sue's tabbouleh salad
directions: Put wheat in large bowl and cover with hot water (just enough to cover).
Let stand while you dice other ingredients.
Add all ingredients; stir to mix.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour or overnight.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat butter and brown sugar until fluffy. Beat in egg and vanilla. Add flour, baking soda, salt and spices. Mix well. Stir in oats.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 9 to 10 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool. Store in tightly covered containers.

title: canadian tea cakes
directions: Mix flour and butter together; put in greased pan.
Pat down lightly
with
fingers
and
bake at 325° for 15 minutes. Completely cool.
Then mix all eight ingredients.
Spread over baked
mixture
above.
Bake
until mixture is brown, about 30 minutes, at 325°.
Completely cool.
Add icing.

title: danish wedding cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream the butter, 1/2 cup confectioners sugar, vanilla and salt until fluffy.
Stir in flour, then nuts and chocolate chips until well blended.
Chill 30 minutes, or until firm enough to handle.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet (slightly flatten top of each cookie using back of spoon dipped in cool water).
Bake in preheated 375° oven until light golden in color, for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: cinnamon rolls(yields 24 large rolls)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix liquid ingredients first and slowly add dry ingredients.
When dough is fluffy, roll 1/4-inch thick, brush with butter or margarine and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Roll like a jelly roll and slice with a very sharp knife. Place on greased baking sheet 1-inch apart.
Let raise and bake for 20 minutes.
Frost.

title: quick barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir until the sugar dissolves. Makes 1 cup.

title: audrey richter's chili souffle
directions: Beat eggs, flour and baking powder together with a fork.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, uncovered, in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, until golden brown. Let stand 5 minutes, then cut into squares.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets.
Let cool slightly; peel and slice. Fry bacon slowly until crisp; drain on paper towel.
Crumble bacon over potatoes.
In the bacon grease, saute onion, green pepper and celery until glossy looking.
Blend in flour, salt, pepper and sugar.
Stir until bubbly, then add vinegar and water. Bring to a boil while stirring.
Pour over potatoes and mix carefully.
Serve warm.

title: orange cookies
directions: Beat sugar, oleo and eggs together.
Sift flour, salt and soda, then add to sugar mixture.
Add juice and coconut.
Drop and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together with hand mixer on medium speed until blended.
Chill and serve with chips.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Beat eggs and add.
Stir flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Add gradually to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla, coconut and nuts.
Make into a roll and let stand overnight.
Slice and bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: crisp 10 minute cabbage
directions: Heat milk and add cabbage.
Simmer about 5 minutes.
Mix flour and butter; stir in a little of the hot milk.
Stir this mixture into the cabbage and cook 4 to 5 minutes or until thickened, stirring constantly.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve hot. Makes 4 servings.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skins.
Cool, peel and shred coarsely.
In saucepan, over low heat, combine cheese and 1/4 cup margarine, stirring constantly, until almost melted.
Remove from heat. Blend in sour cream, onions, salt and pepper.
Fold in potatoes and place in 2-quart casserole.
Dot with remaining margarine. Can be refrigerated overnight or bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken liver pate
directions: Melt 1/2 cup butter or margarine in saucepan.
Add chicken livers, onions, curry powder, paprika, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook over low heat for eight minutes.
Blend mixture in electric blender or food processor until smooth.
Add the cognac and remaining butter and blend in.
Chill until firm either in a terrine or mold the mixture into the shape of a pineapple and completely cover with the sliced olives.
Cap with a fresh pineapple top, if desired.

title: lois' twinkie frosting
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients until it thickens.
Then cool it. Add margarine and sugar, mixed together.
Beat all together very well for 5 minutes.
Very good on chocolate cake!

title: onion rings
directions: Mix all ingredients together except flour and onions. Separate onion into rings.
Place onion first into bowl of flour, then in batter.
Do this three times and on the last time around, leave onions in flour for a couple of minutes so it will stick. Deep fry at 350° until golden brown.

title: blueberry crumble
directions: Heat the berries with sugar.
Thicken with cornstarch and water.
Pour thickened berries over crumble mixture in pan.
Press the remaining crumble on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with whipping cream or ice cream.

title: tortellini soup
directions: Remove casings from sausage.
Brown sausage and cook until crumbly. Remove meat from pot. Reserve 1 tablespoon drippings.

title: pork casserole
directions: Dice pork and brown it.
Cook noodles and drain.
Mix all together.
Cover with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
tags: cream of chicken soup with water

title: mounds bars
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar and butter. Press into 13 x 9-inch cake pan. Bake 10 minutes at 375°. Pour condensed milk over top and sprinkle with coconut. Bake for 10 more minutes or until lightly browned. Melt a large package of chocolate chips and 1 tablespoon peanut butter over water in top of double boiler. Spread on top of candy. Let cool.
Cut in squares.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix water and all-bran.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Cream margarine and sugar into this.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add Raisin Bran and buttermilk.
Combine and mix all three mixes only until moistened.
Put in greased muffin tins.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate coconut cheesecake bars
directions: Combine first two ingredients, cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Stir in coconut, press mixture firmly in greased 8 inch square pan.
Cream together cheese, melted chocolate, eggs, sugar and flour with electric mixer.
Gradually add cream, vanilla and cinnamon mixing until smooth.
Pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes, or just until filling is set.
Cool, then refrigerate.
Cut into bars before serving.

title: rosette macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and cool.
Add veggies, mustard, salt and pepper, mixing well.
Fold in mayonnaise, mixing well.
Gently fold in chopped eggs. Refrigerate until serving time.
Garnish with egg wedges; sprinkle with parsley and paprika.

title: fire specier(four-specie dollars)
directions: Sift flour; add all other ingredients.
Knead well; shape into a round roll.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill in the refrigerator until the next day.
With a sharp knife, cut into thin slices. Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes 40 biscuits.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend together the chili sauce and cream cheese; mix in the salad dressing, onion and horseradish.
Fold in shrimp, cover and chill at least 1 hour.
Serve with crackers.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Peel and dice carrots.
Dice onion. Dice green pepper.
Add vegetables to boiling water until tender. Add vegetables and water they were boiled in, to 1 quart simmering milk.
Add ham.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer about 30 minutes.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix cracker crumbs with 1/2 cup melted margarine.
Put in a 14 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cream 1 cup margarine and gradually add sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Spread mixture over cracker crust and cover with sliced bananas. Sprinkle with pineapple.
Spread whipped topping over pineapple.
Garnish with cherries and nuts. Chill thoroughly.
Serves 20.

title: cowboy beans
directions: In a 2-quart casserole dish, combine all ingredients. Mix well. Bake, uncovered, in 375° oven for 40 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well, pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 1 hour at 300 ° or until done.

title: homemade banana ice cream
directions: For 1 1/2 gallon ice cream freezer.
Mix all ingredients, except milk, in large bowl. Mix thoroughly, dicing up bananas. Pour into ice cream freezer and fill with milk to "fill" line on freezer. Cover with ice and rock salt.
Takes approximately 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Mix cake as directed and bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together pudding, cream cheese and milk; beat until smooth.
Spread on cooled cake.
Top with pineapple and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: linda's cone surprise
directions: Pour milk into bowl; add pudding mix.
Beat slowly with hand beater or at low speed of mixer until well blended, about 1 to 2 minutes.
Blend in whipped topping; add nuts and chill.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes according to directions.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Pour in greased casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: beef balls
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Roll into small meatballs and drop into next 3 ingredients.
Simmer on low until done.

title: red sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, gradually add sugar, beat until fluffy.
Add egg, beat in oil.
Combine flour, cream of tartar and soda and add. Stir in vanilla.
Chill dough 2 hours (I usually chill overnight). Shape in 1 inch balls, dip tip in sugar, flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Store in airtight container.
Layer with wax paper.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: salisiccig, alla rigatoni
directions: Remove sausage from casing; brown with onion and garlic.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt, oil and parsley.
Bring to a boil and simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes.	Cook rigatoni as directed. Serve with sauce.

title: vegetable bake
directions: Saute eggplant in oil in skillet. Brown lightly on both sides. Set aside. Saute zucchini, mushrooms, green pepper, green onion and garlic several minutes. Add tomatoes, salt and pepper. Alternate layers of vegetables and cheese in shallow buttered baking dish. End with cheese. Microwave for 12 minutes or bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: homemade turkey chili
directions: Brown ground turkey in margarine.
Add chili mix and chili powder; stir well.
Add kidney beans and tomatoes; stir until mixed well.
Turn heat on low.
Simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook pie crust first. Fix filling and pour into pie crust. Mix flour, cocoa and sugar. Add milk and stir well. When it boils, take it off the stove. Add butter, flavoring and eggs.
Put back on stove, simmering until it's thick.
Pour into pie crust.
Let cool, cover and then refrigerate.

title: cheese crispies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter; add chopped broccoli to onion in skillet.
Heat low until broccoli thaws.
In large mixing bowl, add all other ingredients (cheese cut up in small pieces).	Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until rice is done.

title: seafood symphony
directions: Marinate shrimp in wine; set aside.
While gathering other ingredients, toss in crab meat and mayonnaise; mix well with spoon.
Put into greased casserole.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix; top with pats of butter.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: frozen peanut butter banana pie
directions: In a medium bowl with mixer at low speed, beat milk, instant pudding and peanut butter until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Reserve 1 cup whipped topping.
Gently fold remaining topping into peanut butter mixture until blended.
Spoon half of the mixture into pie crust.
Slice 1 banana and arrange over filling.
Top with remaining peanut butter mixture.
Freeze 4 to 6 hours or overnight.
Before serving, swirl reserved whipped topping on pie.
Slice second banana and arrange decoratively on top.
If desired, drizzle with chocolate syrup.
Serves 8.

title: crock-pot italian roast beef
directions: Trim all excess fat from roast.
Mince 1 onion, the garlic, celery and salt pork.
Lightly flour roast; rub with minced mixture.
Slice remaining onion; place in crock-pot.
Place roast on onion.
Cover and cook on low setting for 10 to 12 hours. Makes 6 to 8 servings (about 3 1/2 quarts).

title: apple crisp
directions: Spray Pam
in 1 1/2 quart oblong dish.
Add sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Cube
bread,
melt oleo and stir together until well coated.
Add
spices
to
apples; top with buttered bread cubes and
bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve as dessert with ice cream or plain
as
a
side
dish.
Recipe may be doubled and baked in 2 1/2 quart dish.

title: party spread
directions: Combine in small bowl. Chill several hours before serving. Great on party rye slices or served as a dip with fresh veggies.

title: boeuf bourguignon
directions: Put all ingredients, except potatoes and carrots, into a large casserole.
Cover.
Bake 3 hours. Add vegetables.
Cover and bake 1 more hour.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and squeeze dry the spinach. Blend all ingredients except bread in blender or food processor, then chill 2 hours.
Cut center of bread out and place bite size pieces around bread shell. Pour dip mixture inside bread shell.
Spread dip on bread and enjoy.

title: johnny cake
directions: Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch or 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix together and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: doreens chicken bites
directions: Dice chicken breast into medium cubes. Wrap with bacon and use toothpick to secure bacon. Arrange in Pyrex dish. Cover with brown sugar. Bake at 375° until bubbly and bacon appears done.

title: mom's apple snitz pie
directions: Make the pie crust.
Mix flour and sugar.
Add sour cream. Stir until smooth.
Add milk gradually.
Peel and quarter apples. Put in unbaked pie crust.
Pour liquid over apples.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 minutes or until apples are done.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: our favorite whole wheat irish soda bread
directions: Sift together white flour, wheat flour, rye flour, soda and sugar.
Add orange peel, caraway seed and raisins.
Add to dry ingredients the buttermilk, eggs and oil.
Barely mix.
This is a sticky dough, so it is wise to spread a layer of cornmeal on the baking sheet before placing dough thereupon.
Flour would also work.
Bake about 50 minutes at 350°.

title: instant irish coffee
directions: Mix well.
Store in cool dry place.
Use 2 teaspoons or more to 1 cup hot water.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Combine in crock-pot.
Cook on low for approximately 1 1/2 hours (or melt quickly in microwave, if in a hurry).
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: creole coleslaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
Peel and shred carrots.
Chop green onions. Mix mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar, sour cream and salt and pepper. Toss all ingredients together and serve.

title: butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: sweet rice
directions: Mix together and serve with pork chops.

title: stewed sweet tomatoes
directions: Peel and cut tomatoes into pieces.
Put into pot with 3 cups water and cook over medium heat.
Bring to boil.
Add butter or margarine, sugar and crumbled cold biscuits into tomatoes.
Cook over low heat.

title: french roasted chicken and potatoes(elegant dining, 1994)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.

title: fig cake
directions: Sift first 6 ingredients.
Combine and beat sugar, oil and eggs together.
Add dry ingredients with buttermilk and vanilla. Fold in fig preserves and nuts.
Bake in 325° oven until done.

title: grandma midgie's teriyaki marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Marinate at least 6 hours.
Grill or bake.
Good for flank steak or chicken.

title: hush puppies
directions: Beat egg and add other ingredients.
Shape into balls and fry in deep fat (preferrably where fish has been fried).
When golden brown, remove from fat and drain on paper towel and serve hot.

title: beef roast
directions: Mix soups together.
Pour over roast in 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with foil.
Bake at 250° overnight or for several hours. Soups make sauce for over potatoes or rice.

title: vermicelli cheese bake
directions: Cook pasta as package label directs; set aside.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 10-cup souffle dish.
Sprinkle with the Parmesan.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine crushed croutons and Parmesan cheese in plastic bag or bowl.
Melt butter in baking dish.
Dip chicken breasts in melted butter, then coat with crouton/cheese mixture.
When all are coated, place chicken in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Drizzle top with some melted butter.
Sprinkle with paprika and parsley.
Bake uncovered 45 minutes.

title: stateside cheddar soup
directions: Melt butter in a heavy soup pot.
Add celery, leeks and carrots; cook over low heat for 3 minutes, stirring constantly. Add flour and cook, stirring, over low heat for an additional 2 minutes.
Add broth and beer.
Bring to a simmer very slowly so vegetables become tender (about 15 to 20 minutes), stirring occasionally.
Over low heat, gradually add cheeses, whisking constantly until smooth.
Season with cayenne pepper, black pepper and salt.
Continue cooking over low heat until heated through. Do not boil, or soup will separate.
Serve in mugs; garnish with snipped chives.
Serves 6.

title: dutch sugar cookies
directions: Mix soda and vinegar, mix in rest of ingredients.
Flatten with fork or glass and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.

title: mini ritz bits mix
directions: Combine crackers, peanuts and pretzels in buttered roasting pan.
Mix butter, sugar and corn syrup in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and baking soda.
Pour over cracker mixture and stir until coated.
Bake at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes, for 1 hour.
Lay on wax paper to cool.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook onion and celery in butter until soft.
Add flour and coat flour in butter evenly.
Add milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add bouillon and simmer until dissolved and soup is thick.
Add cooked broccoli.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Cook and crumble sausage, drain.
Add sausage to other ingredients, adding chopped stems to mixture.
Mix well.
Stuff clean mushrooms and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.

title: danish sand cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour and almond.
Mix well.
Bake in "extra" long loaf pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes in a 350° oven.
Do not open oven door during baking.

title: spiced fruit punch
directions: Combine all ingredients, except ginger ale and ice.
Let chill for at least 3 hours.
Strain; add ginger ale and ice.
Makes about 3 quarts before adding ice.

title: meat loaf
directions: Crumble crackers and add to rest of ingredients.
Mix well. Place in loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pear kuchen
directions: Drain pears.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add sifted flour, baking powder and salt.
Press into 8 to 9-inch pan or pie plate. Arrange pears, cut side down.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Beat egg yolk, brown sugar and cream.
Pour over pears.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes longer till browned.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese and stuff into peppers. Wrap each pepper in foil.
Bake for 2 hours at 350°.
Open foil and add either cheese and melt for 5 minutes.

title: hershey's great american chocolate chip cookie
directions: Cream butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt. Gradually beat into creamy mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool slightly. Remove from cookie sheets.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: german chocolate angel pie
directions: Beat egg whites with the salt and cream of tartar until foamy. Add sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating to very stiff peaks. Fold in vanilla and nuts.
Spoon into lightly greased 8-inch pie pan.
Bake at 300° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool.
Stir chocolate in the water over heat until melted.
Cool until thickened.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Whip cream and fold in chocolate mixture.
Pile into shell.
Chill 2 hours.

title: syrek(slovak easter cheese)
directions: Pour milk into saucepan and break eggs into milk, making sure each yolk is broken.
Add salt, sugar and vanilla and mix.
Do not cook over direct flame, since this mixture scorches easily.
Use a double boiler, have low heat and stir frequently.
Cook slowly until mixture looks like scrambled eggs.
Pour mixture into cheesecloth and tie tightly.
Hang and let drain for about 1 hour. Gently squeeze cheesecloth bag to remove any excess liquid and hang for about 3 hours.
Remove cheese from bag and refrigerate until cool.
Decorate with cloves or pepper balls.

title: pizza dough
directions: Measure warm water into bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast; stir until dissolved.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Beat them into the yeast and water mixture.
Work until smooth.
Let rise in greased bowl. Punch down and put on greased pizza pans.
Top with favorite sauce and toppings.

title: vanilla wafer fruit cake
directions: Mix fruit, crushed wafers and nuts.
Mix eggs, sugar and cream. Add spice, flavor and pour over fruit, wafers and nuts.
Mix well. Press into a greased Bundt (or tube) pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°. Cool for 15 minutes only and remove from pan.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix brown sugar, syrup, eggs and oleo together.
Pour over pecans in uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until firm.

title: pickled peach salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water, cool. Drain peaches, take off kernel. Add gelatin to 2/3 cup juice. Add a little bit of water to the peach juice. Add celery, nuts and chopped peaches. Let set until congealed.

title: potato latkes
directions: Grate potatoes and onions in electric blender or with fine blade of food grinder.
Place in bowl, add eggs, seasonings and matzoh meal.

title: calzone
directions: Sift dry ingredients twice.
Add shortening.
With fork or knife, cut through until it looks as fine as meal.
Add beaten eggs and milk at once; mix with large spoon until well blended. Turn out on floured board; knead gently for a few minutes, until smooth.
Cut dough into 2 parts.
Chill dough while preparing filling.

title: sopaipillas(fried biscuit puffs)
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in the shortening until mixture resembles cornmeal.
Gradually add the water, stirring with a fork (dough will be crumbly).
Turn onto floured surface; knead into small ball.
Divide dough in half. Let stand for 10 minutes.

title: italian dressing
directions: Combine
ingredients
in a jar.
Cover and shake vigorously. Shake again before serving.
Makes 1 2/3 cups.

title: grandma mary's corndulata
directions: Spray Pam on large casserole.
Spread chili 2 inches deep in dish.
Layer with corn chips 1 inch thick.
Corn is 1/4 of can. Continue until all ingredients have been layered to top and spread cheese over top.
Top with 1 can French fried onions (optional). Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry delight
directions: Let jello, water and sugar slightly jell.
Mix and let harden.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix cake and bake according to box.
Cool cake.
Make holes in cake with toothpick.
Boil pineapple and sugar until sugar melts. Pour over cake.

title: liz's chicken casserole
directions: Spray 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with Pam.
Place chicken in pan first.
Place slices of cheese over chicken.
Mix soup with milk or water and spread over cheese.
Melt butter and toss with stuffing (made).
Sprinkle over soup mixture.
Be careful, may drip in oven. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or so.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken; debone.
Chop.
Boil eggs; peel and chip finely. Put eggs and chicken in a large bowl.
Add chopped bell pepper, chipped sweet pickles, chipped celery, chipped onion and the desired amount of mayonnaise.
Sprinkle with black pepper.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Chop peaches, add lemon juice; set aside.
Fold Eagle Brand milk with Cool Whip.
Fold in peach mixture.
Spoon in Ready Crust.
Chill at least 4 hours.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Spray pan with Pam. Layer the bottom with a row of Tater Tots. Mix soup and ground beef together. Pour on top of Tots. Top with cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water 30 minutes or until tender. Cool, peel and cut into 1/4 to 1/2-inch strips; set aside.
Combine 1/4 cup butter and next 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Add potatoes and cheese.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine 3 tablespoons butter and stuffing mix; sprinkle over potato mixture.

title: noodle bake
directions: Brown ground beef.
Cook noodles until almost done; drain. Add the tomato soup and 1 can water.
Grate cheese and mix with noodles.
After mixed, add beef.
Put into baking dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cold noodles with sesame sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over noodles and serve.

title: hearty beef barley soup
directions: Heat oil on medium heat in a 4 1/2 quart stockpot.
Add onions and ground beef or turkey; and cook until meat is browned.
Drain off fat.
Add broths, water, barley and mushrooms.
Cover pot and bring to a boil.
When boiling, add garlic, worcestershire sauce, thyme and the au jus mix.
Stir until the au jus mix dissolves. Boil keeping pot covered. Add carrots and re-cover the pot. Continue to boil 5 more minutes or until barley is tender.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: candied yams
directions: Boil sweet potatoes, cool; peel and slice potatoes.
Starting with potatoes, put one layer in baking pan or casserole.
Sprinkle sugar on top, followed with pats of margarine until covered. Continue with potatoes, sugar and margarine alternately.
When that process is completed, sprinkle vanilla, cinnamon and nutmeg on top.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: cherry pie filling salad
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl and stir.

title: watercress and egg sandwiches
directions: Mash eggs until smooth.
Add mayonnaise and mustard (I use fork.)
Mix in watercress.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: orange salad #2
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: lora ferguson's squash casserole
directions: Cook sliced squash in a little water until tender; drain. Saute onions, bell pepper and celery in butter in casserole dish. Add cooked squash, beaten eggs and soup.
Put cracker crumbs on top and cook at 325° for 25 minutes.
Garnish with grated cheese.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Simmer 1 hour and serve.

title: cheesy mexican chicken
directions: Place chicken in 13 x 9 inches baking dish.
Mix soup, 1 1/2 c cheese, milk, and seasoning mix.
Spoon over chicken.
Top with chips, cover.
Bake at 375°
for 30 minutes.
remove cover, top with 1/2 c cheese.
Bake uncovered 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve with rice.

title: favorite pancakes
directions: Beat egg; add remaining ingredients in order listed and beat with
rotary
beater or wire whisk until smooth.
Grease heated griddle,
if necessary.
Pour batter from tip of large spoon or from pitcher onto hot griddle.
Turn pancakes as soon as they
are puffed
and
full of bubbles, but before bubbles break.
Bake other side until golden brown.

title: best ever cake
directions: Stir well.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake in 350° oven 40 to 45 minutes.
Frost cake as soon as it comes from oven.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar, butter, shortening and eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, flavoring, milk and baking powder (the flour and milk alternately, then add flavoring and baking powder).
Beat until creamy.
Bake in a greased pan at 325° for 1 hour.
Increase heat to 350°.
Bake 30 minutes more.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter together; beat in egg.
Sift all dry ingredients except baking soda together, stir in nuts and raisins, set aside.
Puree persimmon pulp until smooth then stir in baking soda.
Add persimmon mixture and dry ingredients alternately into creamed butter and sugar mixture; mixing well after each addition. Drop batter by heaping teaspoon on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes about 2 dozen cookies.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a 14 x 10-inch pan or deep casserole dish.
Cover with biscuit dough, leaving a few air holes.

title: pickled okra
directions: Wash okra which is fresh picked and tender.
Pack in sterilized jars.
To each pint jar add:
1 hot pepper pod, 1 garlic clove and 1 teaspoon dill seed.

title: barbecue hot dogs
directions: Cook onion in oil until soft.
Add ketchup, tomato sauce, mustard, vinegar and brown sugar.
Simmer until cooks down a bit and add slashed hot dogs.
Cook until sauce thickens and dogs are done.
Meat balls can also be simmered in this sauce.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Put layer of pecan pieces in pan, then layer of coconut.
Make cake mix as directed on package and pour over nut and coconut layers.
Mix cream cheese and butter, then add sugar.
Mix until smooth and creamy.
Spread on top of cake mix.
Bake for 1 hour or until done. Let cool completely.
Serve from pan.

title: recipe for a happy child
directions: Boil together with care, kindness, security, love, loving parents and faith in God.
Keep hot at all times, never let get cool.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake forever.
Makes one happy child!

title: chocolate-toffee brownie cake
directions: Position rack in center of oven and preheat oven to 350°. Butter 9 inch diameter cake pan with 2 inch high sides.
Sprinkle pan with 1/2 Tbsp. cocoa powder;
tilt pan to coat bottom and sides, shake out excess.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt in small bowl.
Stir butter and remaining cocoa in heavy small saucepan over low heat until butter melts and mixture is smooth. Remove from heat.

title: payday bars
directions: Mix cake mix with 2/3 cup margarine and 1 egg. Press into greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Add mini marshmallows on top and bake for another 5 to 7 minutes. Let cool completely. In medium saucepan, melt together peanut butter chips, 2/3 cup Karo syrup and 1/4 cup butter. Pour over marshmallows. Top with 1 cup chopped peanuts.

title: fresh apple bread
directions: Combine butter and sugar; mix until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and buttermilk with soda dissolved in it.
Stir in flour, vanilla, apples, raisins and nuts.
Put into 2 greased and floured loaf pans (8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inches).
Melt butter, brown sugar and cinnamon and drizzle over the loaves.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: lemon dessert
directions: *For firmer texture, use 2 1/2 cups milk.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Mix all.
Bake in jelly roll pan at 350° for 45 minutes. Frost with powdered sugar frosting.

title: meat and veggie balls
directions: Mix all ingredients (except soup); shape into 1 1/2-inch balls. Brown a little in butter.
Place in a baking dish; then add your tomato soup over top.
Bake about 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: watermelon cooler
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender until smooth.
Makes 4 cups.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add taco seasoning, except 2 teaspoons, to hamburger.
Mix dressing, sugar and 2 teaspoons of taco seasoning.
Mix all other ingredients.
Leave dressing until you serve the salad.

title: fried chicken
directions: Cut chicken into sections; rinse off under tap water (cool). Drain water off chicken; set aside.
Mix together all dry ingredients in bowl or plastic bag.
Place chicken in bag; shake. In frying pan, heat oil until hot on medium temperature.
Place chicken in pan and fry until golden brown.

title: cherry balls
directions: Roll in graham cracker crumbs.
Put cherry in a little bit of mixture.

title: fresh tomato relish
directions: Combine ingredients and let stand at room temperature for 1 hour. Chill for at least 3 hours. Makes 4 cups.

title: apricot brandy pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and rest of ingredients.
Beat well after each addition.
Bake at 325° in a tube pan for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pear mincemeat
directions: Grind together pears, apples oranges (with skin) and lemon (with skin).
Add raisins and other ingredients.
Stir everything together and cook over slow heat about 1 hour and 20 minutes or desired consistency.
Can in jars or freeze.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Toast bread and cut in squares, like croutons.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Starting with toast, alternate layers in a casserole dish.
Bake at 375 degrees for 20 - 30 minutes.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Cut in butter until mixture is consistency of coarse crumbs.
Mix in sour cream, stirring to form soft dough.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface.
Roll or pat dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with floured 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: sunny fruit fiesta
directions: Using a melon baller, scoop flesh from cantaloupe and honeydew into balls;
set aside.

title: annie mary's chow chow
directions: Combine and pour over vegetable mixture.
Boil both mixtures for 3 minutes.
Fill jars and seal.

title: miracle cheese cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Cream together cheese, sugar and vanilla; add gelatin and lemon juice and blend well.
Fold in stiffly whipped Milnot.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pineapple and pie filling into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread dry cake mix evenly over fruits.
Place margarine in small squares on top of cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake 50 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Cook sugar, water and cornstarch until thickened, then add jello and mix well. When cool, pour over peaches that you've arranged in the bottom of a baked pie crust.
Put in refrigerator. To serve top with Cool Whip.

title: hot dog stew
directions: Adjust amounts to your needs.
In large saucepan, saute onions, celery and parsley.
Slice hot dogs in bite-size pieces and add. Saute just about 1 minute.
Add water (prefer 1/2 beef or chicken stock).

Pare and slice potatoes thick and carrots slice thin. Cover and stew until it becomes thickened with the smaller pieces of overcooked potatoes (or take equivalent of 1 or 2 potatoes with a little of the juice in blender, then return to thicken).
Add peas, corn and limas.
Substitute smoked sausage for the hot dogs.

title: bean soup
directions: Put all ingredients in a big pot.
Simmer over low heat 3 to 4 hours, until beans are done.
Add more water as needed.

title: aunt max's dill pickles
directions: Bring mixture to a boil.
In sterilized jars, put in 2 large heads of dill and 2 cloves of garlic; pack cucumbers.
Pour boiling hot brine over cucumbers to 1/2 inch from top and seal. Pickles will be ready in 6 to 8 weeks.
(If hot pickles are desired, place 1 hot pepper in jar.)
Makes 4 quarts.

title: german sweet chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water.
Cool.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with buttermilk to chocolate mixture, beating after each addition until smooth.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased and floured pans, three (8-inch) or (9-inch) layer pans or 2 rectangle pans.
(I use 2 rectangles.
It works fine.)
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Cool.

title: date balls
directions: Cook together for 6 minutes the sugars, dates and evaporated milk.
Add and mix together in a large bowl the Rice Krispies, coconut, nuts and date mixture.
Form into balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: beef vegetable casserole
directions: Press meat into casserole dish (13 1/2 x 8 1/2 x 1-inch). Slice all vegetables.
Place a layer of potatoes on meat, next a layer of sliced carrots, then a layer of celery (I chop the celery); end with onions.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour soup over this and cover tightly.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: fresh rhubarb pudding
directions: Mix 1 can crushed pineapple with 2 cups fresh rhubarb.
Grease a 10 x 6-inch casserole and put fruit in bottom.
Beat egg slightly and add 3/4 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon lemon juice and 2 tablespoons flour; pour over fruit.
Sift 2/3 cup flour and 3 tablespoons sugar and a pinch of salt.
Cut 2 tablespoons margarine into this mixture.
Sprinkle over fruit.
Bake 45 minutes.
Garnish with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy enchilada dish
directions: Heat the tortillas according to directions on the package. Brown the beef, then add the onion and 1 1/2 cups cheese; mix well. Fill each tortilla with about 1/4 cup of the mixture. Roll the tortilla and place in a shallow baking dish. Heat chili and pour over tortillas; sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese. Bake in a 400° oven until cheese is melted and mixture is hot.

title: neiman-marcus cake(very rich)
directions: Mix and pat into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: barbecue meat balls
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Form into balls the size of a walnut and brown in 2 tablespoons shortening.
Remove to baking dish and add sauce.

title: strawberry-rhubarb pie
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups sugar, salt and flour.
Arrange half strawberries and rhubarb in pastry lined 9-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle with half of sugar mixture.
Repeat with remaining fruit and sugar mixture; dot with butter.
Adjust top crust and flute edges.
Brush top of pie with cold water and sprinkle on tablespoon of sugar. Bake in hot oven (425°) 40 to 50 minutes or until rhubarb is tender and crust is browned.
Serve warm with sour cream or scoop of vanilla ice cream.

title: teriyaki pork ribs with kraut
directions: Place rack of ribs in a glass container.
Mix teriyaki sauce, orange marmalade, minced garlic and ginger.
Pour over ribs. Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Rinse and drain sauerkraut. Spread kraut in shallow baking pan.
Place ribs on kraut.
Pour sauce over all.
Bake at 350° until brown, turning one time.

title: pineapple icebox cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool. Beat softened cream cheese until fluffy.
Slowly add milk, then pudding and beat 2 minutes or until thick.
Spread pudding over cake.
Drain pineapple very well.
Sprinkle over pudding mixture. Spread Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with finely chopped nuts. Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: orange cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, cream together 1 1/2 cups sugar and butter.
Mix in eggs, flour, salt and baking soda.
Mix in orange rind and sour cream.
Mix orange juice and 1/2 cup sugar in separate bowl; set aside.
Grease form pan with butter.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: david eyre's pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a mixing bowl, combine flour, milk, eggs and nutmeg.
Beat lightly, leaving batter a little
lumpy. Melt butter in a 12-inch skillet with a heatproof handle.
When very hot, pour in batter.
Bake in oven 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Sprinkle with sugar and return briefly to oven. Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Serve with jelly or jam as a dessert or breakfast.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Add a few cracker crumbs on top.
(Use enough milk to get into crackers and still some left in dish.)
Bake in a casserole dish for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: mock champagne punch
directions: Soak lutefisk in cold water for 3 to 4 hours.
Remove dark skin and fins.
Cut in serving size pieces.
Place in a cheesecloth and put to boil in a kettle or cold water, to which salt has been added.
Cook about 5 minutes until fish is tender; then drain and serve with drawn butter or cream sauce.
Serves 4 Swedes or 40 Germans.

title: easy bake lasagna
directions: Mix together cottage cheese, eggs, oregano and basil.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Mix all ingredients and fry by spoonfuls in margarine.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except stuffing mix.
Alternate layers of stuffing mix with layers of squash mixture in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered, and 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion.
Drain well and mash.
Mix dressing mix, sour cream and soup well and either add to or dot with oleo. Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle finely crumbled dressing on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until browned and set.

title: spaghetti
directions: Prepare noodles according to instructions on package.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Add onion.
Blend in flour, seasonings and milk.
Add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Add remaining ingredients. Place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with additional cheese and bake until melted.

title: pink punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid with sugar and water.
Add pineapple juice and orange juice.
Using the can from the orange juice, add 3 cans of water.
Stir well.
Makes about 3 gallons.
Serve over ice or may be frozen.
Remove from freezer several hours before serving.

title: drunken hot dogs
directions: Cut hot dogs into 1-inch pieces. Make a sauce of remaining ingredients and mix all together. Bake in casserole dish at 275° for 2 hours.

title: fruit dessert
directions: Mix orange juice and pudding; drain pineapple juice, add with pudding.
Do not use mandarin orange juice at all.
Add pineapple chunks and oranges.
Then add bananas right before serving.
Add some coconut, improves taste.
(Also can use coconut pudding). Recipe can be doubled.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Tastes better when made a day ahead and refrigerated.
Great with raw veggies.

title: mandarin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.

title: dill and onion bread(breadmaker)
directions: Add dry ingredients into breadmaker in order given.
Add onion.
Microwave water for 2 minutes.
Add shortening and, when melted, pour into breadmaker.
Hit start.
Have breadmaker set on white bread.
If baking in oven, set breadmaker on manual and, after last rising in buttered pan, bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, eggs, milk and one stick margarine and put into a large casserole dish.
Mix flour, brown sugar, margarine, pecans and vanilla.
Sprinkle over sweet potatoes.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: corny dogs
directions: Mix all together except hot dogs. Dip hot dogs in batter. Fry in deep fryer until brown.

title: homemade beef jerky
directions: Trim off all visible fat from the flank steak.
Cut lengthwise with grain into long thin strips, no more than 1/4-inch thick. Combine soy sauce with garlic salt and lemon pepper.
Pour over beef strips and toss until well coated.
Place wire rack on baking sheet.
Arrange strips on rack to touch, but not overlap.
Bake in a very slow oven (150° to 175°) overnight, 10 to 12 hours.
Store finished jerky at room temperature in airtight container.
If all fat has been removed, beef jerky will keep indefinitely.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate.
Cook beef and onion until brown.
Drain.
Stir in seasoning mix.
Spread into pie plate.
Beat milk, Bisquick and eggs until smooth (1 minute by mixer).
Pour into pie plate.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes and cheese.
Bake until knife comes out clean, 8 to 10 minutes. Top with sour cream, tomatoes, lettuce and cheese if desired.

title: peanut butter cornflake cookies
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil.
Let boil for 30 to 45 seconds.
Remove from the heat.
Add peanut butter and margarine. Stir until melted.
Add cornflakes. Pat down loosely in buttered pan. Cut when set.

title: ernie's greens
directions: Wash greens.
Chop garlic fine.
Heat olive oil in pan over high heat.
Add chopped garlic and brown. Add greens and toss to coat with oil and garlic.
Salt to taste while tossing.
Sprinkle with apple cider vinegar or lemon juice.

title: cheerio pudding
directions: Melt 1 stick butter in pudding pan.
Mix into a batter the 1 cup sugar, flour, salt, baking powder and milk.
Pour on top of butter.
Bring to boil the water, 1 cup sugar, cherries and almond extract.
Pour this on top of batter.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Batter will rise to top and brown.

title: easy custard pie
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Cover edge of pastry with 1 1/2-inch wide strip of aluminum foil.
Thoroughly mix eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Slowly stir in hot milk.
Pour immediately into unbaked pie shell (to avoid spills, fill at oven).
Sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Bake about 20 minutes or until silver knife inserted from side of filling comes out clean.
Serve warm or cold.

title: low-fat microwave lasagne
directions: Crumble turkey into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover loosely and microwave on High (100%) for 3 minutes; break up and stir.
Cover and microwave another 2 to 3 minutes more; drain, if necessary. Add to turkey, spaghetti sauce, tomato sauce, 1 tablespoon parsley and the oregano; stir well.
Cover tightly and microwave on High to boiling, 3 to 4 minutes.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan for 35 minutes.
When done, pour 1 package marshmallows over cake while hot.

title: sweet pickle sticks
directions: Cut the cukes longways twice.
Put in pan.
Pour boiling hot water over them.
Let stand overnight.
Next morning, drain.
Pack in jars.
Boil the remaining ingredients 5 minutes.
Pour into jars over cukes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package.
Drain.
Arrange 1/2 broccoli in 2-quart casserole.
Cover with peas.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, salt, pepper, cheese, onion and eggs to make a sauce. Pour 1/2 sauce over broccoli and peas.
Add rest of broccoli and top with remaining sauce.
Sprinkle crushed crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: tomato with sweet corn soup
directions: Heat oil in frying pan.
Sprinkle in wine and pour in soup stock immediately, then add sweet corn and mix well.
Cook until soup boils.
Season with salt.
Add mushrooms, tomatoes and lima beans.
When it boils again, reduce the heat to low and pour in the cornstarch paste slowly.
Stir well until thickened.
Beat egg white and sprinkle into soup carefully.
Turn off heat immediately.
Pour into soup bowl and serve.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Boil sugar, corn syrup and water in heavy pan.
Boil for 5 minutes or until firm ball stage.
Beat egg whites stiff and gently pour syrup on them.
Beat until stiff, then add nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: sauteed mushrooms
directions: Melt oleo in skillet; toss mushrooms until softened. Add seasonings and lemon juice. Serves 3.

title: sesame crackers
directions: Mix all dry ingredients well.
Add oil, water and mix with fork.
Pour into dry ingredients and mix well.
Knead until smooth.
Divide into two equal parts and knead for 5 minutes. Roll out to 1/8-inch thick or less.
(Roll directly on cookie sheet.)
Cut into desired shapes.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes. You may need to spray your pans or cookie sheets with Pam.

title: baked spinach with ham frittata
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, combine eggs, basil and pepper; beat until combined.
Set aside.
In a 10-inch ovenproof skillet, cook onion in hot margarine until tender, but not brown.
Remove from heat; stir in spinach and ham or turkey ham.
Add egg mixture.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Butter a 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Spread a layer of coconut and then a layer of pecans.
Mix cake mix according to box recipe and then pour batter into pan.
Mix confectioners sugar, cream cheese and butter with a mixer.
Pour this mixture on top of chocolate mix, staying away from the edges.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Season meat and brown in oil in skillet.
Add chopped celery, onions, bell pepper and parsley.
Cook until wilted.
Pour off oil and add tomatoes.
Cook at low heat for 15 minutes.

title: toffee crunch bars
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with a mixer until creamy; add cake mix, eggs and water, beating until blended.
Stir in brickle chips and pecans.
Drop by tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Top will look moist.

title: homemade beef soup
directions: Mix all together in a large pan and simmer for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: carrot bars
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: bea's fudge
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar and milk and start timing. Boil 10 minutes.
Turn off heat and add the chocolate chips and butter. Mix and then add the marshmallows.
Keep beating until it's shiny. Add the pecans and vanilla.
Pour into buttered pan. Cool and enjoy.
Must be miniature marshmallows.

title: chicken-n-rice
directions: Blend broth and soup in large saucepan.
Add other ingredients.
Cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Brown flour in oil over medium heat.
Add celery, onions and garlic.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and okra; cook 5 additional minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, except shrimp. Add 3 pints of water and simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add shrimp and simmer for 30 minutes.
Server over hot rice and season with Tony Chachere Creole seasoning.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach as directed; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate for an hour.
Using an ice cream scoop, form balls and place on a flat pan.
Freeze; store in a plastic bag until ready to bake and serve.
Place frozen balls on thick tomato slices and bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes at 350°. Makes 24 balls.

title: merengue de banana(banana meringue)
directions: Peel the bananas and halve them lengthwise. Fry them in a little oil and arrange them at the bottom of a round Pyrex bowl. Mix the 6 egg yolks with 1/2 pound sugar and 4 ounces of butter. Pour over the bananas. Beat the egg whites until stiff. Slowly add the remaining sugar. Turn the mixture, but do not beat for 1/4 hour. Put the meringue into a piping bag and squeeze decoratively over the bananas. Cook in a very warm oven (230°) for 40 minutes. Serve hot or cold.

title: trout amandine
directions: Saute almonds in butter or margarine in a heavy skillet until golden brown.
Do not burn.
Transfer to a bowl and set aside.

title: quick nacho dip
directions: Heat all ingredients in medium saucepan until creamy.
Serve with taco chips.

title: caramel pralines(choudrant, louisiana)
directions: Caramelize 1 cup sugar in heavy iron skillet.
Cook over very low heat until sugar turns to syrup.
While sugar is melting, place other 2 cups of sugar, milk, butter and salt in heavy saucepan.
Bring to boiling point.
Very slowly pour syrup from skillet into other ingredients, stirring constantly.
Be sure to turn heat to low before starting the pouring.
Cook until good firm ball stage (drop a bit of mixture into cool water to test firmness).
Cool slightly.
Add vanilla and pecan halves.
Stir until mixture loses gloss.
Drop by tablespoon onto wax paper.

title: p b and o snackers(cookies)
directions: Mix the oatmeal, flour, cinnamon, salt, nutmeg and baking soda; set aside.
Beat together the butter, peanut butter, brown sugar and granulated sugar at medium speed until light and fluffy, approximately 4 minutes.
Beat in the vanilla.
Add the eggs, one at a time; beat 1 minute after each.
Add the chocolate chips or raisins.
Beat in oat mixture on lowest speed just until blended. Chill dough.
Make balls and flatten.
If you do not chill, drop by spoonfuls.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: green beans
directions: Cook onion in heated Wesson oil in saucepan for about 5 minutes.
Add all ingredients, except chili sauce and pepper; cook until beans are tender.
Stir in chili sauce and pepper.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash and tear spinach.
Put spinach in large bowl, then arrange as follows:
bean sprouts, water chestnuts, eggs and bacon.
Do not toss!!!
Beat with mixer:
salad oil, sugar, vinegar, catsup, salt, onion and Worcestershire.
Pour over salad 1 hour before serving.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Cream peanut butter, butter, sugar and brown sugar. Add egg, salt, vanilla, flour and soda. Roll in 1-inch balls and place in ungreased mini muffin tins. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven and put peanut butter cups in each cookie until top is seen. Let set 10 minutes before removing from tins.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Melt butter and combine remaining ingredients.
Place in buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: angel food cake dessert
directions: Mix pudding, milk, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Place cake in 9 x 13 glass dish. Pour pudding mixture over cake.
Pour pineapples over the top.
Do not mix.
Chill.

title: bananas foster
directions: Cut banana in circles.
Melt butter in a frypan and add brown sugar and cinnamon.
Simmer until blended.
Add liqueurs; simmer briefly, then add cut bananas.
Simmer until bananas become almost clear.
Spoon ice cream into serving portions and top with sauce. Serves 2.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries and sugar together and let them set overnight in the refrigerator.
Take out and add the celery, Cool Whip and pecans.
Mix well; keep refrigerated.
This is good at Thanksgiving and Christmas.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine the 1st six ingredients.
Mix and form into a loaf. Mix next 4 ingredients in a small saucepan and simmer for a few minutes.
Spread mixture over meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: grandpa's hot stuff
directions: Cut roast into pieces.
Lightly flour and fry in pan.
Then place meat in skillet or wok and cover with water.
Add paprika and cayenne pepper.
Cook on low for 2 hours.
Thirty minutes before you eat, add cut up potatoes.
The broth is wonderful for dipping your bread in and should be hot enough to clear your nose.
If not, add more cayenne.

title: punch(lip licking good; 36 cups)
directions: Mix thoroughly and serve from punch bowl.
Add 1/4 of a gallon of vanilla ice cream on top.

title: zesty carrot bake
directions: Cook carrots until tender. Place in a 1-quart baking dish; set aside. In a small bowl, combine the next 5 ingredients; mix well. Pour over carrots. Combine bread crumbs and butter; sprinkle on top. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese. Return to oven for 2 to 3 minutes or until the cheese melts.

title: homemade tortilla chips
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
Spray 2 cookie sheets with cooking spray.
Stack tortillas and cut in 6 wedges.
Place tortillas on cookie sheets in a single layer.
Lightly spray with cooking spray.
Sprinkle lightly with salt.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown onions with ground beef; drain. Add salt, pepper, chili powder and Worcestershire sauce. Add rice and tomatoes. If you brown your ground beef in an electric skillet, the whole casserole can be baked in it. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all together.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Beat eggs.
Add white sugar, potatoes, 3/4 stick oleo, milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Put in a lightly buttered oblong casserole dish.
Prepare topping by mixing brown sugar, flour and 1/4 stick oleo.
Spread on top of casserole.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Sprinkle lightly with cinnamon and 2 to 3 tablespoons sugar. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet over moderate heat (about 250°).
Add onion, garlic and green pepper and cook until tender.
Stir in rice and cook until lightly browned, stirring occasionally.
Add mushrooms, soy sauce and oregano; cover and simmer 20 minutes over low heat (about 200°), stirring occasionally.
Heat oven to 350°. Pour rice mixture into a deep buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add consomme and water.
Cover and bake 1 1/4 hours.
Serves 6.

title: ken's stuffed shrimp
directions: Peel shrimp down to last joint above tail. Then butterfly by cutting along vein without cutting all the way through.
Wash in cold water and drain.

title: easy chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook chicken and debone it and set aside.
Cook rice as directed on box.
Mix cooked rice and all three cans of soup. Pour into casserole dish.
Add chicken, salt and pepper.
Heat in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbly hot.

title: ms. grace's peanut brittle
directions: Place peanuts, sugar, karo, water, butter and pinch of salt into heavy saucepan. Put pan on stove over high heat and bring to boil, stirring continuously. Stirring continuously, boil vigorously for about 13 minutes or until mixture reaches hard crack on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat immediately.
Add vanilla and soda, stir to mix thoroughly and quickly pour onto buttered aluminum foil.
Tease with forks to spread to desired thickness and allow to cool (about 1 hour). Break into pieces approximately 1x2 inches in size.

title: hamburger and olive steak
directions: Season meat and add onions.
Press into flat greased baking dish pan.
Sprinkle sliced onion.
Press into.

title: springy garden dip
directions: Blend sour cream, mayonnaise, sugar, salt and pepper.
Stir in minced vegetables.
Chill.
Serve with these vegetables (carrot sticks, cucumber strips, celery sticks, green peppers) and various crackers.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and 1/2 cup pecans; chill.
Form into ball. Roll in remaining chopped pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: holiday meatballs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, except butter. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Melt butter in a large skillet; brown meat balls, a few at a time, over medium heat, 5 to 8 minutes.* Then bake, uncovered, for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: cream of celery soup
directions: Put celery, onion and chicken broth in pot.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes or until the celery is tender.
Put in blender and puree.
Return to pot and add half and half and salt and reheat slowly.

title: banana cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients, three times. Cream butter; add sugar gradually until light and fluffy. Add eggs and beat well. Add bananas and beat again. Add flour to creamed mixture, alternating with milk, beating after each addition until smooth. Add vanilla. Bake in 2 layer pans at 375 degrees for 25 minutes. Cool completely.

title: popcorn balls
directions: In a saucepan, cook all ingredients to 250° or until a 1/2 teaspoon makes a ball.
Butter hands.
Pour sauce over popcorn and toss.
Make balls; put on wax paper to cool.

title: string beans and tomatoes
directions: Wash and cut beans.
Saute onions in oil over medium heat about 5 minutes.
Add tomato paste, tomatoes, water, garlic, salt and sugar and bring to a boil.
Add beans and cook about 35 minutes or until tender.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: microwave crumb crust
directions: Total Cooking Time:
2 1/2 to 3 minutes.

title: chocolate stove top cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan and cook until mixture begins to boil.
Remove from heat and cool 1 minute before adding remaining ingredients.
Stir well and drop by teaspoons onto wax paper.

title: green bean deluxe
directions: Cook beans in water with bouillon cube until tender.
Drain and save broth; set the beans aside.
Saute onion with bacon or smoky links until onion is tender.
Add broth to onion mixture and bring to a boil.
Thicken with cornstarch.
Add beans and mix until beans are all covered with broth.
Serve hot.

title: rolled beef bites
directions: Mix thoroughly together and spread on thin slices of roast beef, turkey or ham.
Roll up and refrigerate to blend.
To serve, cut rolls in 1-inch slices and serve with a toothpick in each one.

title: broccoli salad
